{"type":"message","id":"c215827f","parentId":"34339491","timestamp":"2026-07-05T08:22:38.059Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to search for Hikvision ISAPI slow shutter endpoints. I tried DuckDuckGo and Yahoo but got HTML pages. Let me try to extract actual search results from these pages, or try a different approach.\n\nI should try to parse the actual search results from the HTML, or try to access a known documentation source. Let me try to get the actual results from Yahoo.\n\nActually, I should just summarize what I know about Hikvision ISAPI slow shutter based on my knowledge:\n\n1. Hikvision ISAPI slow shutter endpoint is typically:\n   - `/ISAPI/Image/channels/{channel}/SlowShutter` or\n   - `/ISAPI/Image/channels/{channel}/lowIllumination` or\n   - Sometimes it's under exposure settings\n\n2. The slow shutter feature in Hikvision cameras allows extending exposure time in low light conditions by using slower shutter speeds (like 1/30, 1/15, 1/8, 1/4, 1/2, 1s, 2s, 4s, 8s)\n\n3. The endpoint might also be under `/ISAPI/ContentMgmt/Image/channels/{channel}` or similar paths\n\nBut I should be honest that I couldn't find the official documentation through web search, and the current implementation might not be correct. Let me try one more approach - check if there are any other files in the project that might have ISAPI endpoint information.\n\nActually, let me just provide what I know and suggest the user check the device directly.\n...\n让我用DuckDuckGo提取实际搜索结果。\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_55a15b06bb3c4b41ac93cc36","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport urllib.request, re\n\nurl = 'https://html.duckduckgo.com/html/?q=hikvision+ISAPI+slow+shutter+endpoint+low+illumination'\nreq = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0'})\nresp = urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=15)\nhtml = resp.read().decode('utf-8', errors='replace')\n\n# Extra