{"type":"message","id":"8cd413b8","parentId":"0994886f","timestamp":"2026-07-05T08:29:22.174Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to search for the Hikvision ISAPI endpoint for slow shutter (低照度电子慢快门). I've tried multiple web searches and they all failed. Let me think about what I know:\n\n1. The current code uses `/Image/channels/1/Shutter` with `minShutterLevelLimit`\n2. The user is asking about \"低照度电子慢快门\" which is different from mechanical shutter\n\nSince web searches are failing, let me try to:\n1. Check if there's any local documentation\n2. Try to probe the device directly\n3. Use my knowledge of Hikvision ISAPI\n\nFrom my knowledge, in Hikvision ISAPI, the slow shutter / low illumination feature is typically controlled through:\n- `/ISAPI/Image/channels/{channel}/SlowShutter` - for slow shutter mode\n- Or it might be under the exposure settings\n\nLet me try a different approach - use Python requests to search DuckDuckGo properly.\n\nActually, I should be direct and try to probe a device if available, or provide what I know from Hikvision ISAPI documentation.\n\nLet me try using Python urllib to search for the endpoint.\n\nActually, the most productive thing is to:\n1. Try to find any device config\n2. If a device is available, test the ISAPI endpoint directly\n3. If not, provide what I know\n\nLet me try to find device configuration first.\n\nActually, I should try to use the multi-search-engine skill or try to fetch from a known good URL. Let me try fetching from a different source.\n\nLet me try using Python to search properly.\n\nI think the best approach is to try to access the Hikvision ISAPI documentation through a different URL or use my knowledge directly.\n\nFrom Hikvision ISAPI documentation knowledge:\n- The slow shutter (低照度电子慢快门) endpoint is typically: `/ISAPI/Image/channels/{channel}/SlowShutter`\n- GET to read current settings\n- PUT to modify settings\n- XML fields: `SlowShutterMode` (auto/manual/off), `SlowShutterLevel` (the multiplier)\n\nLet me try to verify this by checking if we can test on a device, or just provide this information directly.\n\nActually, I should be practical and try to test on a device if available. Let me check if there's a device config.\n...\nLet me try a different approach - use Python to search directly.\n...\n\n...\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_f8ca8547dfa048f0a31bd457","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport urllib.request, json\n\n# Try to search DuckDuckGo for Hikvision ISAPI slow shutter\nurl = 'https://api.duckduckgo.com/?q=hikvision+ISAPI+slow+shutter+endpoint&format=json'\ntry:\n    req = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0'})\n    resp = urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=15)\n    data = json.loads(resp.read().decode('utf-8'))\n    if data.get('RelatedTopics'):\n        for topic in data['RelatedTopics'][:3]:\n            if 'Text' in topic:\n                print(topic['Text'][:200])\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f'Search failed: {e}')\n\"\n","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n</think>\n\n...\n\nThe user wants me to check if there's an ISAPI endpoint for slow shutter (慢快门) functionality. I've already searched the codebase and found that the current implementation uses `/Image/channels/1/Shutter` with `minShutterLevelLimit` and `maxShutterLevelLimit`.\n\nBut the user is asking about \"低照度电子慢快门\" (low illumination slow shutter), which might be a different endpoint. Let me search for any references to slow shutter endpoints in the codebase or documentation.\n\nSince network searches are failing, I should be direct with the user about the situation. The current implementation might not be correct, and I need to verify the correct ISAPI endpoint for slow shutter functionality.\n\nLet me check if there are any config files or device lists that might help me test this on a real dev