✅ set_whitebalance\n2. ✅ set_noisereduce\n3. ✅ update_image_settings (color)\n4. ✅ set_exposure\n5. ✅ set_shutter\n6. ✅ set_iris (separate edit)\n7. ✅ set_sharpness (separate edit)\n\nI need to check if set_slow_shutter has save_settings. Let me read the function.\n\nActually, from my earlier work, I already added save_settings to set_slow_shutter in the batch edit. Let me verify.\n\nLooking at the edit history, the batch edit had these items:\n- [0] set_exposure - ✅\n- [1] set_shutter - ✅\n- [2] set_iris - ❌ (failed)\n- [3] set_sharpness - maybe (after the failed one?)\n- [4] set_slow_shutter - maybe\n\nActually, in the edit tool, edits are processed in order. If edit[2] fails, the tool might stop processing or might continue. The error says \"Could not find edits[2]\" which implies the edit tool found the first two but failed on the third. The other edits might or might not have been applied.\n\nLet me check the current state."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.read:171","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":30,"offset":3735,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\api\\router.py"}},{"type":"text","text":"The user sent \"...\" again. I need to continue working. Let me check if set_slow_shutter has save_settings, then continue with the remaining work.\n\nI need to:\n1. Check and fix set_slow_shutter if needed\n2. Add GET /settings endpoint\n3. Modify console.html\n4. Update VERSION and HEARTBEAT.md\n\nLet me read the set_slow_shutter function to check if it has save_settings."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.exec:172","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub && python -c \"with open('src/api/router.py','r',encoding='utf-8') as f: lines=f.readlines()\nfor i,line in enumerate(lines):\n    if 'async def set_slow_shutter' in line:\n        for j in range(i,min(i+45,len(lines))):\n            print(f'{j+1}: {lines[j].rstrip()}')\n        break\n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\