: device_id, \"level\": dss_level})\n            return {\"success\": True, \"message\": \"慢快门: \" + (\"关闭\" if dss_level == \"off\" else dss_level)}"}],"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\api\\router.py"}},{"type":"text","text":"The user sent \"...\" again. I've been working on modifying router.py to add save_settings to all the set_* endpoints. I need to continue with the task.\n\nSo far I've completed:\n1. set_whitebalance - ✅\n2. set_noisereduce - ✅\n3. update_image_settings (color) - ✅\n4. set_exposure - ✅\n5. set_shutter - ✅\n6. set_iris - ✅\n7. set_sharpness - ✅\n8. set_slow_shutter - ✅ (just added)\n\nNow I need to:\n1. Add GET /settings endpoint\n2. Modify console.html\n3. Update VERSION and HEARTBEAT.md\n4. Restart and test\n\nLet me continue. The user keeps sending \"...\" which means I should continue working. I've completed all the router.py modifications for the set_* endpoints. Now I need to:\n1. Add GET /settings endpoint\n2. Modify console.html\n3. Update VERSION and HEARTBEAT.md\n4. Restart and test\n\nLet me add the GET /settings endpoint first. I need to find a good place to add it in router.py. It should be in the Image settings section.\n\nActually, let me add it after the set_slow_shutter function or near the existing image settings endpoints.\n\nThen I need to modify console.html to:\n1. Call GET /settings on connect to restore settings\n2. Suppress toasts during restore (already have _isInitializingImageParams)\n3. Add the restore logic\n\nLet me continue."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.edit:174","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"@api_router.get(\"/ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-saved\", summary=\"获取设备保存的设置\", tags=[\"Image\"])\nasync def get_saved_settings(device_id: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"获取设备保存的图像参数设置 (用于记忆恢复)。\"\"\"\n    try:\n        from src.advanced.device_settings import load_settings\n        mac_clean = device_id.replace(\":\", \"\").replace(\"-\", \"\").lower()\n        if len(mac_clean) != 12:\n            return {\"success\": False, \"message\": \"无效的设备标识\"}\n        \n        settings = load_settings(mac_clean)\n        return {\"success\": True, \"data\": settings or {}}\n    except Exception as e:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"获取保存设置失败: {e}\"}","oldText":"@api_router.get(\"/ptz/{device_id}/osd/ptz\", summary=\"获取PTZ OSD状态\", tags=[\"OSD\"])"}],"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\api\\router.py"}},{"type":"text","text":"The user sent \"...\" again. I've been working on modifying router.py to add save_settings to all the set_* endpoints, and now I'm adding the GET /settings endpoint. Let me continue.\n\nI just added the GET /settings endpoint. Now I need to:\n1. Modify console.html to restore settings on connect\n2. Update VERSION and HEARTBEAT.md\n3. Restart and test\n\nLet me modify console.html. I need to:\n1. Add a `restoreSettings(deviceIp)` function that loads saved settings and applies them\n2. Modify `loadAllImageParams()` to call `restoreSettings()`\n3. Make sure `setWhiteBalanceMode()` and other set functions suppress toast during init\n\nActually, looking at the current code, `loadAllImageParams` already calls `loadWhiteBalance`, `loadNoiseReduce`, etc., which read from the device. The issue is that these functions set UI values and trigger `onchange` events, which then call the set functions and show toasts.\n\nThe current flow:\n1. `loadAllImageParams()` sets `_isInitializingImageParams = true`\n2. Calls `loadWhiteBalance(deviceIp)`\n3. `loadWhiteBalance` reads from device, sets `wbModeSelect.value`, calls `onWbModeChange(wbModeSelect.value)`\n4. `onWbModeChange` calls `setWhiteBalanceMode(mode)` which sends API and shows toast\n5. `setWhiteBalanceMode` shows toast even though `_isInitializingImageParams = true`\n\nWait, looking at the code:\n```javascript\nfunction setWhiteBalanceMode(mode) {\n    var dev = window.connectedDevice ? window.connectedDevice.ip : null;\n    if (!dev) return;\n    apiPost('/api/v1/ptz/' + dev + '/image/whitebalance', { mode: mode })\n        .then(function(r) {\n            if (r && r.success) {\n                showToast('success', '白平衡: ' + (mode === 'auto' ? '自动' : '手动'));\n                if (typeof operationLog === 'function' && !_isInitializingImageParams) operationLog(...);\n            }\n        });\n}\n```\n\nThe toast is shown unconditionally! It's not checking `_isInitializingImageParams`. This is the bug.\n\nSo the fix for the \"白平衡自动\" toast is:\n1. In `setWhiteBalanceMode()`, add `if (!_isInitializingImageParams) showToast(...)`\n2. Similarly in other set* functions\n\nBut the user also wants to save and restore settings. So:\n1. Backend: Save settings when user changes them (already done in router.py)\n2. Frontend: On connect, restore saved settings from `GET /api/v1/ptz/{device_id}/settings`\n\nFor the restore:\n1. `loadAllImageParams()` calls `restoreSettings(deviceIp)`\n2. `restoreSettings` gets saved settings from API\n3. For each saved setting, call the appropriate set function (but suppress toast)\n\nActually, the simplest approach is:\n1. Keep the current loadAllImageParams flow (reads from device, updates UI)\n2. After loadAllImageParams, call restoreSettings which overrides with saved values\n\nBut this would still trigger toasts if setWhiteBalanceMode is called.\n\nActually, the best approach:\n1. In `setWhiteBalanceMode` and other set functions, check `_isInitializingImageParams` before showing toast\n2. Add `restoreSettings(deviceIp)` that:\n   - Gets saved settings\n   - For each setting, calls the set function (which sends API to device)\n   - The set function already has `_isInitializingImageParams` check\n\nLet me modify console.html:\n1. Fix setWhiteBalanceMode to suppress toast during init\n2. Add restoreSettings function\n3. Call restoreSettings in loadAllImageParams\n\nWait, there's a subtlety. The user said \"上次我没有做任何设置，所以不应该有这个弹出提醒\"。 This means:\n- The toast shows \"白平衡自动\" \n- But the user didn't set it to auto\n- So it's showing because the device is in auto mode by default\n\nThis means: the restore should NOT be done during init, because the user hasn't set anything yet. The restore should only be done when the user has previously saved settings.\n\nBut the current behavior is: device is in auto mode, and the toast shows. The user wants the toast suppressed during init, regardless of whether there are saved settings.\n\nSo the fix is:\n1. Suppress toasts during init (fix the bug)\n2. Optionally restore settings from saved settings\n\nLet me focus on:\n1. Fix the toast bug (check `_isInitializingImageParams` in set functions)\n2. Add restoreSettings that loads saved settings and applies them\n3. Call restoreSettings in loadAllImageParams\n\nLet me modify console.html.\n\nThe key changes in console.html:\n1. In `setWhiteBalanceMode`, add `if (!_isInitializingImageParams)` before showToast\n2. Similarly in `setWhiteBalanceGain`, `setNoiseReduce`, `setShutterSpeed`, `setIrisLevel`, `setSharpness`, `setSlowShutter`, etc.\n3. Add `restoreSettings(deviceIp)` function\n4. Call `restoreSettings(deviceIp)` in `loadAllImageParams`\n\nThis is a lot of changes. Let me do them one by one.\n\nActually, let me check which set functions are in console.html:\n- setWhiteBalanceMode\n- setWhiteBalanceGain\n- setNoiseReduce\n- setShutterSpeed (or similar)\n- setIrisLevel (or similar)\n- setExposureMode (or similar)\n- setSharpness\n- setSlowShutter\n\nLet me read the relevant parts of console.html.\n\nActually, looking at the code I already read:\n- Line 1209: `function onWbModeChange(mode)` - this calls `setWhiteBalanceMode(mode)`\n- Line 1488: `function setWhiteBalanceMode(mode)` - shows toast\n- Line 1502: `function setWhiteBalanceGain(channel, value)` - shows toast\n- Line 1549: `function loadSlowShutter(deviceIp)` - this is a load function\n- Various other set functions\n\nI need to:\n1. In `setWhiteBalanceMode`, suppress toast when `_isInitializingImageParams`\n2. In `setWhiteBalanceGain`, suppress toast when `_isInitializingImageParams`\n3. In `setNoiseReduce`, suppress toast when `_isInitializingImageParams`\n4. etc.\n5. Add `restoreSettings(deviceIp)` function\n6. Call `restoreSettings(deviceIp)` in `loadAllImageParams`\n\nBut wait, the user said \"上次我没有做任何设置，所以不应该有这个弹出提醒\". This means the toast is showing during init even though the user didn't do anything. The fix is to suppress the toast during init.\n\nSo the changes needed in console.html:\n1. Fix all set functions to suppress toast during init\n2. Add restoreSettings function\n3. Call restoreSettings in loadAllImageParams\n\nLet me focus on the most important change: suppressing toast during init. This is what fixes the user's immediate complaint.\n\nThen the restore feature is a bonus.\n\nActually, the user wants both:\n1. No toast during init (suppress toast)\n2. Restore last settings (memory feature)\n\nLet me do both.\n\nFor the restore feature:\n1. Backend saves settings (already done)\n2. Frontend loads saved settings and applies them\n3. During restore, toasts are suppressed\n\nThe restore should happen after the current load functions (which read from device). Because:\n1. First, read from device and update UI (current behavior)\n2. Then, override with saved settings\n3. Send API to device to apply saved settings\n\nBut if we send API to device, the set functions will show toast. So we need to suppress toasts during restore.\n\nWait, there's a better approach. Instead of sending API to device during restore, we can just set the UI values and not send API. The API to device should only be sent when the user manually changes a value.\n\nBut then the device would not be updated. The user wants \"恢复最后一次的设置\", which means the device should be set to the saved values.\n\nSo we need to:\n1. Load saved settings from API\n2. For each saved setting, send API to device\n3. Suppress toasts during this process\n\nBut the current `setWhiteBalanceMode` sends API to device AND shows toast. I need to modify it to suppress toast during init.\n\nActually, let me look at the current code more carefully:\n\n```javascript\nfunction loadAllImageParams(deviceIp) {\n    _isInitializingImageParams = true;  // v7.59: 开始初始化,禁止记录日志\n    loadExposure(deviceIp);\n    loadOsdStatus(deviceIp);\n    loadWhiteBalance(deviceIp);\n    // ...\n    setTimeout(function() { _isInitializingImageParams = false; }, 3000);\n}\n```\n\nAnd in `loadWhiteBalance`:\n```javascript\nfunction loadWhiteBalance(deviceIp) {\n    apiGet('/api/v1/ptz/' + deviceIp + '/image/whitebalance').then(function(r) {\n        if (r && r.success && r.data) {\n            var wb = r.data;\n            // ...\n            if (wbModeSelect) {\n                if (wb.mode === 'manual') {\n                    wbModeSelect.value = 'manual';\n                } else {\n                    wbModeSelect.value = 'auto';\n                }\n                onWbModeChange(wbModeSelect.value);\n            }\n        }\n    });\n}\n```\n\nAnd `onWbModeChange` calls `setWhiteBalanceMode(mode)`.\n\nSo the flow is:\n1. `loadAllImageParams` sets `_isInitializingImageParams = true`\n2. `loadWhiteBalance` reads from device\n3. `loadWhiteBalance` calls `onWbModeChange(wbModeSelect.value)`\n4. `onWbModeChange` calls `setWhiteBalanceMode(mode)`\n5. `setWhiteBalanceMode` sends API to device\n6. `setWhiteBalanceMode` shows toast (BUG: should check `_isInitializingImageParams`)\n\nWait, but if we suppress the API call during init, the device won't be set. But that's OK during init, because we're just loading the current device state.\n\nActually, the issue is: `loadWhiteBalance` reads from device and then calls `onWbModeChange`, which calls `setWhiteBalanceMode`, which sends API to device AGAIN. This is redundant.\n\nThe correct fix:\n1. In `onWbModeChange`, only call `setWhiteBalanceMode` when NOT in init mode\n2. Or, in `setWhiteBalanceMode`, only send API when NOT in init mode\n\nActually, the simplest fix:\n1. In `setWhiteBalanceMode`, check `_isInitializingImageParams` before sending API\n\nBut that would prevent restoring saved settings.\n\nHmm, let me think about this differently.\n\nThe user's actual problem: \"重启astrohub，连接上设备，右上角就弹出一个提示，白平衡自动，实际上我没有做任何设置，所以不应该有这个弹出提醒\"\n\nThis means:\n- On restart, the device connects\n- `loadAllImageParams` is called\n- `loadWhiteBalance` reads from device (which is in auto mode)\n- `loadWhiteBalance` calls `onWbModeChange('auto')`\n- `onWbModeChange` calls `setWhiteBalanceMode('auto')`\n- `setWhiteBalanceMode` sends API to device\n- `setWhiteBalanceMode` shows toast \"白平衡: 自动\"\n\nThe fix is: suppress the toast during init.\n\nFor the \"恢复最后一次的设置\" feature:\n- When user changes a setting, it's saved to settings.json (backend already does this)\n- When device reconnects, `restoreSettings` loads saved settings and applies them\n- During restore, toasts are suppressed\n\nSo the changes:\n1. In `setWhiteBalanceMode` and other set functions, suppress toast when `_isInitializingImageParams`\n2. Add `restoreSettings` function that loads saved settings\n3. Call `restoreSettings` in `loadAllImageParams`\n\nLet me implement these changes.\n\nActually, I realize there's a simpler approach for the restore:\n- In `loadWhiteBalance`, after reading from device, DON'T call `onWbModeChange`\n- Instead, set the UI values directly\n- Then, in `restoreSettings`, set the saved values and send API\n\nBut this would require rewriting the load functions.\n\nActually, the simplest fix for the toast bug:\n- In `setWhiteBalanceMode`, add `if (!_isInitializingImageParams)` before `showToast`\n- Similarly in other set functions\n\nFor the restore feature:\n- In `restoreSettings`, call the set functions (which will send API but not show toast because of the fix above)\n\nLet me implement this.</think>好的，继续执行。我已经完成了router.py的所有修改。现在需要修改console.html：\n\n1. 修复setWhiteBalanceMode等函数，在初始化时抑制toast\n2. 添加restoreSettings函数\n3. 在loadAllImageParams中调用restoreSettings\n\n让我先检查哪些set函数需要修改：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.exec:175","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub && python -c \"\nwith open('src/web/includes/console.html', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n# 找到所有showToast调用\nfor i, line in enumerate(content.split('\\n')):\n    if 'showToast' in line and 'function set' in content.split('\\n')[max(0,i-5)]:\n        print(f'Line {i+1}: {line.strip()}')\n        # 打印函数名\n        for j in range(max(0, i-10), i):\n            if 'function set' in content.split('\\n')[j]:\n                print(f'  Function: {content.split(\\\"\\\\n\\\")[j].strip()}')\n                break\n        print()\n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}},{"type":"text","text":"The user is sending \"...\" repeatedly. I need to continue working on the task. I've been modifying router.py to add save_settings to all set_* endpoints. Now I need to modify console.html to:\n\n1. Suppress toast during init in set functions\n2. Add restoreSettings function\n3. Call restoreSettings in loadAllImageParams\n\nLet me continue working on this. I need to modify console.html.\n\nFirst, I need to understand the current flow:\n1. loadAllImageParams sets _isInitializingImageParams = true\n2. Calls loadWhiteBalance, loadNoiseReduce, etc.\n3. These read from device and update UI\n4. onWbModeChange triggers setWhiteBalanceMode which sends API and shows toast\n\nThe fix:\n1. In setWhiteBalanceMode, check _isInitializingImageParams before showToast\n2. Add restoreSettings function\n3. Call restoreSettings in loadAllImageParams\n\nLet me read the relevant parts of console.html and make the changes."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.read:176","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":20,"offset":1488,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\web\\includes\\console.html"}},{"type":"text","text":"The user sent \"...\" which is a continuation signal. I need to continue working on the task. I've been modifying router.py and now need to modify console.html to add restore logic and suppress toast during init.\n\nSo far in router.py:\n1. ✅ set_whitebalance - saves settings\n2. ✅ set_noisereduce - saves settings\n3. ✅ update_image_settings (color) - saves settings\n4. ✅ set_exposure - saves settings\n5. ✅ set_shutter - saves settings\n6. ✅ set_iris - saves settings\n7. ✅ set_sharpness - saves settings\n8. ✅ set_slow_shutter - saves settings\n9. ✅ GET /settings endpoint added\n\nNow in console.html:\n1. Fix setWhiteBalanceMode to suppress toast during init\n2. Add restoreSettings function\n3. Call restoreSettings in loadAllImageParams\n4. Fix other set functions similarly\n\nLet me read the setWhiteBalanceMode function and modify it."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.edit:177","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"    apiPost('/api/v1/ptz/' + dev + '/image/whitebalance', { mode: mode })\n        .then(function(r) {\n            if (r && r.success) {\n                if (!_isInitializingImageParams) showToast('success', '白平衡: ' + (mode === 'auto' ? '自动' : '手动'));\n                if (typeof operationLog === 'function' && !_isInitializingImageParams) operationLog('白平衡: ' + (mode === 'auto' ? '自动' : '手动'), 'success');\n            }\n        });","oldText":"    apiPost('/api/v1/ptz/' + dev + '/image/whitebalance', { mode: mode })\n        .then(function(r) {\n            if (r && r.success) {\n                showToast('success', '白平衡: ' + (mode === 'auto' ? '自动' : '手动'));\n                if (typeof operationLog === 'function' && !_isInitializingImageParams) operationLog('白平衡: ' + (mode === 'auto' ? '自动' : '手动'), 'success');\n            }\n        });"}],"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\web\\includes\\console.html"}},{"type":"text","text":"The user sent \"...\" again. I need to continue working on the task. I've been mod