{"type":"message","id":"8ad5ecaa","parentId":"d9259bfd","timestamp":"2026-07-05T13:44:35.320Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The settings-saved endpoint timed out. This is likely because the device is not connected, and the endpoint tries to resolve the device. Let me check the endpoint code.\n\nActually wait - the `settings-saved` endpoint only reads from local file, it doesn't need the device to be connected. Let me check the implementation again.\n\nLooking at the code I added:\n```python\n@api_router.get(\"/ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-saved\", summary=\"获取设备保存的设置\", tags=[\"Image\"])\nasync def get_saved_settings(device_id: str) -> dict:\n    try:\n        from src.advanced.device_settings import load_settings\n        mac_clean = device_id.replace(\":\", \"\").replace(\"-\", \"\").lower()\n        if len(mac_clean) != 12:\n            return {\"success\": False, \"message\": \"无效的设备标识\"}\n        settings = load_settings(mac_clean)\n        return {\"success\": True, \"data\": settings or {}}\n    except Exception as e:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"获取保存设置失败: {e}\"}\n```\n\nThis should be fast - it just reads a JSON file. The timeout might be because the service just started and is still initializing. Let me try again.\n\nActually, the issue might be that the service is still loading. Let me wait a bit more and retry.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_98ed60bfa5a0401784268fc1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Start-Sleep -Seconds 5; try { $r = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"http://localhost:10280/api/v1/ptz/240f9b764193/image/settings-saved\" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 10; Write-Host \"settings-saved: $($r.Content)\" } catch { Write-Host \"Error: $($_.Exception.Message)\" }","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":135104,"output":435,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"tota