{"type":"message","id":"e805b2f2","parentId":"a72c277a","timestamp":"2026-07-05T13:48:37.106Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the situation:\n\n1. The user asked me to continue testing the device settings memory feature (v8.46)\n2. I ran tests to save different settings:\n   - Noise reduction: Set spatial_level to 75 → returned success\n   - Slow shutter: Set dss_level to *4 → returned success\n   - Settings-saved endpoint: Returned only whitebalance data, NOT noise reduction or slow shutter\n\nThe issue is clear: The settings.json file only contains whitebalance data from the previous test, but the noise reduction and slow shutter settings I just saved did NOT get written to the file.\n\nLet me trace through the code:\n\n1. In router.py, I added `save_device_settings(mac_clean, {\"noisereduce\": ...})` in the set_noisereduce endpoint\n2. Similarly for slow_shutter\n\nBut wait - the settings-saved endpoint returned only whitebalance. This means either:\n- The noise reduction and slow shutter save calls aren't being executed\n- OR there's an issue with the save_device_settings function\n\nLet me check the router.py to verify the save calls are actually there. I need to verify all 8 save calls are present and working.\n\nActually, looking at the results:\n- Whitebalance was saved in an earlier test (before the restart)\n- Noise reduction and slow shutter were just set via API (returned success from device)\n- But settings-saved only shows whitebalance\n\nThis suggests the save_device_settings calls for noisereduce and slow_shutter might not be working correctly, OR they might not be present in the code.\n\nLet me check what save_device_settings calls exist in router.py to verify.\n\nActually, I already verified earlier that there are 8 save_device_settings calls. Let me check if they're actually being executed properly.\n\nThe issue might be:\n1. The mac_clean extraction might be failing (device_id might not be a clean 12-char MAC)\n2. The device_id in the URL is \"240f9b764193\" which IS a valid 12-char MAC\n\nWait, let me re-read the code. In the set_noisereduce endpoint, I have:\n```python\ntry:\n    mac_clean = device_id.replace(\":\", \"\").replace(\"-\", \"\").lower()\n    if len(mac_clean) == 12:\n        save_device_settings(mac_clean, {\"noisereduce\": {\"spatial_level\": spatial, \"temporal_level\": temporal}})\nexcept Exception:\n    pass\n```\n\nThis should work. But maybe the exception is being silently caught?\n\nLet me check if the settings.json file actually exists and what's in it.\n\nActually, I should just verify the actual file content and trace through what's happening.\n\nLet me read the actual settings.json file and also verify the router.py has all the save calls.\n\nThe user wants me to continue testing, so I should:\n1. Check the actual settings.json file\n2. Verify all save calls are present in router.py\n3. If there's an issue, fix it\n\nLet me proceed with checking the file and verifying the code.\n发现一个问题！设置没有全部保存。让我检查实际文件和代码：\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_f53491b4c7ce4acdbcf963c7","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\data\\devices\\240f9b764193\\settings.json"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_a60a5abbb2c144a883dfdc6e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub && python -c \"\nwith open('src/api/router.py', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    lines = f.readlines()\n\n# 查找所有 save_device_settings 调用\nfor i, line in enumerate(lines):\n    if 'save_device_settings' in line and 'mac_clean' in line:\n        # 显示上下文\n        start = max(0, i-2)\n        end = min(len(lines), i+2)\n        for j in range(start, end):\n            prefix = '>>>' if j == i else '   '\n            print(f'{prefix} {j+1}: {lines[j].rstrip()[:100]}')\n        print()\n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}