{"type":"message","id":"29bc9090","parentId":"cc64df13","timestamp":"2026-07-05T13:54:36.639Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b140c32d2d3f410aae561da5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        return result\r\n    except Exception as e:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"获取快门异常: {e}\"}\r\n\r\n\r\n@api_router.post(\"/ptz/{device_id}/image/shutter\", summary=\"设置快门\", tags=[\"Image\"])\r\nasync def set_shutter(device_id: str, data: dict) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"设置快门参数 - v7.07: 使用独立 Shutter 端点\"\"\"\r\n    import xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\r\n    mgr: PTZDeviceController | None = _managers.get(\"ptz_controller\")\r\n    if not mgr:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": \"PTZDeviceController未初始化\"}\r\n\r\n    target_ip = _resolve_device_id_to_ip(mgr, device_id)\r\n    if not target_ip:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"无法解析设备标识: {device_id}\"}\r\n\r\n    ctrl, err = mgr._get_controller(target_ip)\r\n    if err:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": err}\r\n\r\n    client = ctrl.client\r\n    try:\r\n        level = data.get(\"level\", \"1/60\")\r\n\r\n        # v7.07: 使用独立 Shutter 端点\r\n        xml_str = f'''<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n<Shutter version=\"2.0\" xmlns=\"http://www.hikvision.com/ver20/XMLSchema\">\r\n  <ShutterLevel>{level}</ShutterLevel>\r\n</Shutter>'''\r\n\n[992 more lines in file. Use offset=3330 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783259676639}}
{"type":"message","id":"cd8aea66","parentId":"29bc9090","timestamp":"2026-07-05T13:54:59.330Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The shutter setting code looks correct. The issue is that when I tried to set it via curl, it returned HTTP 400. Let me check the actual error response and also check what the device expects. The current shutter level is \"1/600\" which is a valid value.\n\nActually, looking at the code more carefully, I see that the set_shutter function uses a POST method but the actual API call uses client.put (HTTP PUT). The issue might be that:\n1. The device doesn't support the \"1/60\" value I tried to set\n2. Or there's a different format expected\n\nActually, the current value is \"1/600\", and I tried to set \"1/60\". \"1/60\" is a standard value that should be supported. Let me check if there's an issue with how the value is being sent or if the device requires a specific format.\n\nBut the more important thing is to test the restore functionality. Let me check the console.html to see if the restoreSettings function is properly connected.\n\nActually, let me focus on testing the complete restore flow. The user wants me to test if the saved parameters are restored when reconnecting to the device.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"让我检查 `restoreSettings()` 是否被正确调用，以及完整的恢复流程：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.read:10","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":5,"offset":860,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\web\\includes\\console.html"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":20682,"output":312,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20994,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783259676639,"responseId":"cht000d98cb@dx19f328f73d42871503"}}
