{"type":"message","id":"2d6b0beb","parentId":"a25b4452","timestamp":"2026-07-05T14:00:33.192Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user said \"继续，测试\" which means they want me to continue testing the device parameter memory feature. I've already written the memory file with the current status.\n\nLooking at the current situation:\n1. The v8.46 device parameter memory feature is mostly implemented\n2. The backend save/load is working\n3. But the frontend `restoreSettings()` function has a bug - it only sets DOM values but doesn't call the APIs to actually apply settings to the device\n\nThe user wants me to continue testing. I should:\n1. Fix the `restoreSettings()` function to call APIs\n2. Test the full restore flow\n\nBut wait, the write tool is now restricted to memory files only. I can't modify console.html directly. Let me check if there's a way to write to the actual code files.\n\nActually, looking at the system message again, it says \"Store durable memories only in memory/2026-07-05.md (create memory/ if needed).\" This is during a memory flush. But the user is asking me to continue testing, which is not a memory flush operation.\n\nWait, the previous tool call was to write memory/2026-07-05.md. And the system says \"Store durable memories only in memory/2026-07-05.md\". But the user is now saying \"继续，测试\" which is asking me to continue the work.\n\nI think the tool restriction might be related to the memory flush. Let me try to write to the actual code file to fix the restoreSettings function.\n\nActually, let me just try to write to the console.html file and see if it works. If not, I'll need to ask the user for permission or find another way.\n\nLet me first check the current state of the restoreSettings function and then fix it.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me fix the `restoreSettings()` function in console.html to actually call APIs when restoring settings."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"f