{"type":"message","id":"1bc03a09","parentId":"36a04bad","timestamp":"2026-07-05T14:04:10.409Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to replace the `restoreSettings()` function in console.html. The current version only sets DOM values but doesn't call the API setter functions. I need to add API calls.\n\nLooking at the code:\n- `onWbModeChange(mode)` already calls `setWhiteBalanceMode(mode)` which calls the API ✅\n- `onSlowShutterChange(level)` already calls `setSlowShutter(level)` which calls the API ✅\n- But shutter, iris, exposure, sharpness, noise reduce, and image settings need explicit API calls\n\nThe setter functions I found:\n- `setWhiteBalanceGain(channel, value)` - for R/B gain\n- `setNoiseReduce(channel, value)` - for noise reduce (spatial/temporal)\n- `setShutterSpeed(value)` - for shutter\n- `setIris(value)` - for iris\n- `setExposureMode(mode)` - for exposure mode\n- `setSharpness(value)` - for sharpness\n- For image settings, need to use `apiPut` to `/api/v1/ptz/{deviceIp}/image/settings`\n\nAlso I notice there's a typo in the current code: `var dnrTemporal = document.getElementById('dnrTemporal');n` - there's a stray `n` at the end. This would cause a JS error!\n\nLet me replace the entire function with the corrected version that calls APIs.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"I see a typo in the current code too: `var dnrTemporal = document.getElementById('dnrTemporal');n` has a stray `n`. Let me replace the whole function:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_2b1369b2ada244d5a90e223e","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":60,"offset":856,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\web\\includes\\console.html"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":3593,"output":412,"cacheRead":49055,"cacheWrite":1665,"totalTokens":54725,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":