{"type":"message","id":"84da02b3","parentId":"1fd987e2","timestamp":"2026-07-05T15:12:26.522Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking why the shutter setting failed with HTTP 400. Let me test:\n1. Current shutter value is 1/600\n2. Setting 1/600 works (success=True)\n3. So the shutter endpoint itself works fine\n\nThe HTTP 400 earlier was probably because I tried to set an unsupported value. Let me check what values are supported:\n- supported_levels: ['1/30', '1/60', '1/125', '1/250', '1/500', '1/1000', '1/2000', '1/4000', '1/8000', '1/30000', '1/25']\n- Current: 1/600\n\nWait - 1/600 is NOT in the supported_levels list! But the device shows it as current_level. This is odd.\n\nThe issue earlier was that I tried to set 1/60 which IS in the supported list, but got HTTP 400. Let me test that:","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_37a7446287be44acbcdf8b61","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport requests\n\n# 测试设置1/60（在supported_levels里）\nr = requests.post('http://localhost:10280/api/v1/ptz/192.168.5.72/image/shutter', \n                  json={'level': '1/60'}, timeout=5)\nprint('设置1/60:', r.json())\n\n# 测试设置1/500（在supported_levels里）\nr2 = requests.post('http://localhost:10280/api/v1/ptz/192.168.5.72/image/shutter', \n                   json={'level': '1/500'}, timeout=5)\nprint('设置1/500:', r2.json())\n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":1829,"output":476,"cacheRead":95063,"cacheWrite":655,"totalTokens":98023,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783264330595,"responseId":"msg_60997fd8-5d48-4d68-bf0d-af3f4c8924f2"}}
