here's a pattern here. Let me test more values to understand which ones work and which don't.\n\nLooking at the supported_levels from earlier:\n['1/30', '1/60', '1/125', '1/250', '1/500', '1/1000', '1/2000', '1/4000', '1/8000', '1/30000', '1/25']\n\nAnd we know:\n- 1/600: works (not in supported list!)\n- 1/1000: works (in supported list)\n- 1/60: fails (in supported list!)\n\nThis is very strange. The device returns 1/600 as the current value, but it's not in the supported list. And 1/60 is in the supported list but fails.\n\nThis suggests that the ISAPI endpoint might have a different set of valid values than what the GET endpoint returns, or there's some other constraint.\n\nLet me test a few more values to understand the pattern better.\n奇怪的结果：\n- 1/60: FAIL (HTTP 400)\n- 1/600: SUCCESS (但不在supported_levels里！)\n- 1/1000: SUCCESS\n\n让我测试更多值，找出规律：\n测试结果很奇怪。让我测试更多值：\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_48ef53a48d3a4d50928203cb","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory && python -c \"\nimport requests\n\n# 测试supported_levels中的所有值\nlevels = ['1/30', '1/60', '1/125', '1/250', '1/500', '1/1000', '1/2000', '1/4000', '1/8000', '1/30000', '1/25']\nfor level in levels:\n    r = requests.post('http://localhost:10280/api/v1/ptz/192.168.5.72/image/shutter', json={'level': level})\n    result = r.json()\n    status = 'OK' if result.get('success') else f'FAIL({result.get(\\\"message\\\", \\\"\\\")})'\n    print(f'{level}: {status}')\n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":635,"output":1187,"cacheRead":100148,"cacheWrite":205,"totalTokens":102175,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783264442114,"responseId":"msg_46b3f921-c37a-4e7e-b790-250f9eb8c4b6"}}
