{"type":"message","id":"7b05522a","parentId":"65aca354","timestamp":"2026-07-05T15:25:53.364Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The `get_shutter` function has a hardcoded `supported_levels` list that doesn't match the actual device capabilities. I need to:\n\n1. Get the MAC address from the device IP\n2. Read the `function.json` file from `data/devices/{mac}/function.json`\n3. Extract `functions.shutter.opt_values`\n4. Use that as `supported_levels` instead of the hardcoded list\n\nLet me make the minimal fix. I'll edit the `get_shutter` function to read from function.json.\n明白了。现在精确修改 `get_shutter` 函数，将硬编码的 `supported_levels` 改为从 `function.json` 读取。\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_f4ecd67737e04c64808ab7cb","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"oldText":"        # 常用快门值\n        result[\"data\"][\"supported_levels\"] = [\n            \"1/30\", \"1/60\", \"1/125\", \"1/250\", \"1/500\",\n            \"1/1000\", \"1/2000\", \"1/4000\", \"1/8000\",\n            result[\"data\"].get(\"min\", \"1/30000\"),\n            result[\"data\"].get(\"max\", \"1/25\")\n        ]","newText":"        # v8.47: 从 function.json 读取真实支持的快门值\n        supported_levels = []\n        try:\n            devices_dir = get_data_path_read(None, None)\n            if devices_dir:\n                devices_dir = devices_dir / \"devices\"\n                if devices_dir.exists():\n                    for device_dir in devices_dir.iterdir():\n                        if device_dir.is_dir():\n                            info_file = device_dir / \"info.json\"\n                            if info_file.exists():\n                                info = json.loads(info_file.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n                                if info.get(\"ip\") == target_ip:\n                                    func_file = device_dir / \"function.json\"\n                                    if func_file.exists():\n                                        func_data = json.loads(func_file.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n                                        if \"functions\" in func_data and \"shutter\" in func_data[\"functions\"]:\n                                            supported_levels = func_data[\"functions\"][\"shutter\"].get(\"opt_values\", [])\n                                    break\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n        \n        if not supported_levels:\n            # 回退: 使用设备返回的min/max\n            supported_levels = [\n                result[\"data\"].get(\"max\", \"1/25\"),\n                result[\"data\"].get(\"min\", \"1/30000\")\n            ]\n        result[\"data\"][\"supported_levels\"] = supported_levels"}],"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\api\\router.py"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n</think>\n\nNow I have all the info I need. Let me make the precise fix:\n\n1. In `get_shutter`, after getting `target_ip`, resolve `target_mac` from the device directory\n2. Read `function.json` for that MAC\n3. Extract `opt_values` from `functions.shutter`\n4. Use that as `supported_levels` instead of the hardcoded list\n5. Fall back to the hardcoded list only if function.json is unavailable\n6. Also fix the default value `\"1/60\"` → `\"1/25\"` (since 1/60 isn't a valid value)\n7. Don't change anything else\n8. Also need to check `set_shutter` default value `\"1/60\"` → should remove the default since it's invalid\n9. Restart service\n10. Test\n\nLet me read the exact lines I need to replace.先读取精确的代码段：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_6cd4820c32b142f7882e1fdf","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":20,"offset":3288,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\api\\router.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_ed39756e1d0e4676b24a7933","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":5,"offset":3283,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\api\\router.py"}}],"api":"anthro