_levels\n\nThe issue is that the current code is only returning min/max as supported_levels, not the actual opt_values from function.json.\n\nLet me think about how to fix this. I need to:\n1. Read the function.json file for the device\n2. Extract the opt_values for shutter\n3. Use those as supported_levels instead of just min/max\n\nThe MAC address for the device is 240f9b764193 (from the data directory structure).\n\nLet me check the function.json structure and then fix the code.\n...\n\n继续修复。让我检查function.json的结构，然后修复代码以正确读取opt_values：\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_57d083da142245119dc84624","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"import json; data = json.load(open('astrohub/data/devices/240f9b764193/function.json')); print(json.dumps(data.get('functions', {}).get('shutter', {}), indent=2))\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":19708,"output":660,"cacheRead":136271,"cacheWrite":1199,"totalTokens":157838,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783265500127,"responseId":"msg_7a34a8dc-3837-44c7-b9c2-253ff0ceffb4"}}
