{"type":"message","id":"c1ea11cb","parentId":"8dff43ae","timestamp":"2026-07-05T15:33:53.503Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to continue the task of fixing the shutter `supported_levels` issue. From the context, I've been working on:\n\n1. The problem: The shutter `supported_levels` endpoint returns hardcoded values like `['1/25', '1/30000']` instead of the actual values from `function.json`\n2. The actual values from `function.json` are: `['1/25', '1/50', '1/75', '1/100', '1/120', '1/150', '1/175', '1/200', '1/225', '1/250', '1/300', '1/425', '1/600', '1/1000', '1/1250', '1/1750', '1/2500', '1/3500', '1/6000', '1/10000', '1/30000']`\n\n3. The current code in `router.py` tries to read from `function.json` but the logic seems to be failing\n4. I need to fix the code to properly read from `function.json` and extract the `opt_values`\n\nLet me look at the current code in `router.py` for the shutter endpoint. The user said to fix it precisely without over-engineering.\n\nThe issue is that the code is trying to match by IP address, but it should be using the MAC address directly since the data is stored in `data/devices/{mac}/` directory.\n\nLet me check the current code and fix it properly. The function.json contains the correct `opt_values`, and I need to make sure the code reads it correctly.\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Good! Now I can see the actual `opt_values` in `function.json`. The problem is the current code in `router.py` is failing to read this properly. Let me check the current code and fix it:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_5b448c72210b4702a21cb2a4","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":50,"offset":3250,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\api\\router.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":2296,"output":519,"cacheRead":137470,"cacheWrite":19702,"totalTokens":159987,"cost":{"input":0,"outpu