{"type":"message","id":"28917f80","parentId":"0c346186","timestamp":"2026-07-05T15:42:27.186Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user hasn't said anything new - this is a tool result continuation. Let me analyze the debug output:\n\n```\nDEVICES_DIR exists: True\nIterating devices:\n  Dir: 192.168.5.72\n  Dir: 240f9b764193\n    IP: 192.168.5.72\n    MATCH!\n    function.json exists: True\n    functions key: True\n    shutter key: True\n    opt_values count: 21\n    opt_values: ['1/25', '1/50', ...]\n```\n\nSo the data IS there and CAN be read. The problem is:\n1. There's a `192.168.5.72` directory AND a `240f9b764193` directory\n2. The `192.168.5.72` directory comes first alphabetically\n3. When iterating, we check `info.json` in `192.168.5.72` first - it doesn't exist or has wrong IP\n4. Then we check `240f9b764193` - it matches and has the function.json with 21 opt_values\n\nSo the code should work... Let me re-read my code change to see if there's an issue.\n\nLooking at the code I added:\n```python\nif not supported_levels:\n    for device_dir in DEVICES_DIR.iterdir():\n        if device_dir.is_dir():\n            info_file = device_dir / \"info.json\"\n            if info_file.exists():\n                try:\n                    info = json.loads(info_file.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n                    if info.get(\"ip\") == target_ip:\n                        func_file = device_dir / \"function.json\"\n                        if func_file.exists():\n                            func_data = json.loads(func_file.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n                            if \"functions\" in func_data and \"shutter\" in func_data[\"functions\"]:\n                                supported_levels = func_data[\"functions\"][\"shutter\"].get(\"opt_values\", [])\n                        break\n                except Exception:\n                    continue\n```\n\nWait, I see the problem! When I check `if info_file.exists():`, it will only process directories that have an `info.json`. The `192.168.5.72` directory might have an `info.json` but with a different IP, so the `if info.get(\"ip\") == target_ip:` check fails, and then `break` is NOT executed (it's inside the `if`), so the loop continues to the next directory.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at my code - the `break` is inside `if info.get(\"ip\") == target_ip:`. So if the IP doesn't match, we continue to the next iteration. That should be correct.\n\nBut wait - maybe the service wasn't restarted properly? Let me check if the service is actually running the new code.\n\nActually, I should re-read the router.py to verify my edit actually went through. The user asked \"继续\" (continue), which means they want me to keep debugging.\n\nLet me verify the code is correct and then restart the service properly.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The user said \"继续\" (continue). The debug output shows:\n- There's both a `192.168.5.72` directory and a `240f9b764193` directory\n- Only `240f9b764193` has the `info.json` with matching IP\n- The function.json exists and has 21 opt_values\n\nSo the data is there. The issue might be:\n1. The service wasn't restarted with the new code\n2. My code edit might not be correct\n3. There might be an exception being silently caught\n\nLet me check the actual code in router.py to verify the edit is there, then restart the service properly.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_57ae6c11423242a2aa6ca0b1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":50,"offset":3330,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\api\\router.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":904,"output":949,"cacheRead":167884,"cacheWrite":1896,"totalTokens":171633,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783266091095,"responseId":"msg_845129dd-c884-44d7-8f6c-e8b69aafc9ec"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a5d75e4e","parentId":"28917f80","timestamp":"2026-07-05T15:42:27.312Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_57ae6c11423242a2aa6ca0b1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        result[\"data\"][\"supported_levels\"] = supported_levels\r\n        result[\"data\"][\"mode\"] = \"manual\"\r\n        return result\r\n    except Exception as e:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"获取快门异常: {e}\"}\r\n\r\n\r\n@api_router.post(\"/ptz/{device_id}/image/shutter\", summary=\"设置快门\", tags=[\"Image\"])\r\nasync def set_shutter(device_id: str, data: dict) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"设置快门参数 - v7.07: 使用独立 Shutter 端点\"\"\"\r\n    import xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\r\n    mgr: PTZDeviceController | None = _managers.get(\"ptz_controller\")\r\n    if not mgr:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": \"PTZDeviceController未初始化\"}\r\n\r\n    target_ip = _resolve_device_id_to_ip(mgr, device_id)\r\n    if not target_ip:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"无法解析设备标识: {device_id}\"}\r\n\r\n    ctrl, err = mgr._get_controller(target_ip)\r\n    if err:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": err}\r\n\r\n    client = ctrl.client\r\n    try:\r\n        # v8.47: 从 function.json 获取默认值，避免硬编码不支持的值（device_id就是MAC）\r\n        default_level = \"1/30000\"\r\n        try:\r\n            device_dir = DEVICES_DIR / device_id\r\n            func_file = device_dir / \"function.json\"\r\n            if func_file.exists():\r\n                func_data = json.loads(func_file.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\r\n                if \"functions\" in func_data and \"shutter\" in func_data[\"functions\"]:\r\n                    opt_values = func_data[\"functions\"][\"shutter\"].get(\"opt_values\", [])\r\n                    if opt_values:\r\n                        default_level = opt_values[0]\r\n        except Exception:\r\n            pass\r\n        level = data.get(\"level\", default_level)\r\n\r\n        # v7.07: 使用独立 Shutter 端点\r\n        xml_str = f'''<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n<Shutter version=\"2.0\" xmlns=\"http://www.hikvision.com/ver20/XMLSchema\">\r\n  <ShutterLevel>{level}</ShutterLevel>\r\n</Shutter>'''\r\n\r\n        put_resp = client.put(\"/Image/channels/1/Shutter\", xml_str)\r\n        if put_resp.status_code == 200:\r\n            log_info(\"image\", \"shutter\", {\"device\": device_id, \"level\": level})\r\n            try:\r\n\n[987 more lines in file. Use offset=3380 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783266147312}}
