{"type":"message","id":"68f9d496","parentId":"645444f8","timestamp":"2026-07-05T15:44:14.019Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I was asked to stop and provide a progress report. Let me compile a comprehensive summary of what has been done so far.\n\nLooking at the conversation history:\n1. User asked about device parameter memory feature - I explained the current state\n2. User asked me to fix the shutter supported_levels issue - I modified the code to read from function.json instead of hardcoded values\n3. User asked about restoreSettings() function bug - I fixed it to actually call APIs\n4. User asked me to fix the restoreSettings() function bug - I did this\n5. User asked me to fix the supported_levels bug - I did this by modifying router.py to read from function.json\n\nLet me trace through the key accomplishments:\n\n**Major Tasks Completed:**\n\n1. **Device Parameter Memory Feature (v8.46)** - Implemented automatic saving and loading of device parameters when connecting/disconnecting devices\n   - Created device_settings.py module with save/load functions\n   - Added settings-saved endpoint\n   - Modified console.html to call restoreSettings() after loading all image params\n   - Fixed restoreSettings() to actually call APIs instead of just setting DOM values\n\n2. **Shutter supported_levels Fix** - Fixed the hardcoded supported_levels list\n   - Modified get_shutter() in router.py to read from function.json\n   - Modified set_shutter() to use function.json for default level\n   - Added fallback logic to handle both MAC and IP as device_id\n\n3. **Code Quality Improvements**\n   - Fixed typo in console.html (dnrTemporal');n -> dnrTemporal');)\n   - Removed hardcoded \"1/60\" values\n   - Added proper error handling with traceback printing\n\n**Files Modified:**\n- astrohub/src/api/router.py - Multiple changes to get_shutter() and set_shutter()\n- astrohub/src/web/includes/console.html - Fixed restoreSettings() function\n- astrohub/src/advanced/device_settings.py - Created new file for device settings management\n\n**Current Status:**\nThe service was restarted and should be running with the new code. The last action was restarting the service after adding traceback printing to debug the supported_levels issue.\n\nLet me provide a detailed report of the work done.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"## 进度报告\n\n### 已完成的主要任务\n\n#### 1. 设备参数记忆功能 (v8.46)\n实现了连接设备时自动加载保存的参数，断开时自动保存当前参数。\n\n**修改的文件：**\n- `astrohub/src/advanced/device_settings.py` - 新建文件，提供参数保存/加载接口\n- `astrohub/src/api/router.py` - 添加8个参数的自动保存逻辑，新增settings-saved端点\n- `astrohub/src/web/includes/console.html` - 添加restoreSettings()函数调用\n\n#### 2. 修复restoreSettings()函数\n**问题：** 函数只设置DOM值，没有实际调用API应用设置\n**解决：** 修改所有参数设置逻辑，调用对应的API函数\n\n**修改内容：**\n- 曝光模式：调用setExposureMode() + updateShutterIrisState()\n- 快门：调用setShutterSpeed()\n- 光圈：调用setIris()\n- 白平衡：调用onWbModeChange() + setWhiteBalanceGain()\n- 降噪：调用setNoiseReduce()\n- 慢快门：调用onSlowShutterChange()\n- 锐度：调用setSharpness()\n- 画面设置：调用apiPut()\n\n#### 3. 修复shutter supported_levels硬编码问题\n**问题：** router.py中supported_levels是硬编码的列表，不包含设备实际支持的值\n**解决：** 从function.json读取真实的opt_values\n\n**修改内容：**\n- get_shutter()函数：添加从function.json读取supported_levels的逻辑\n- set_shutter()函数：添加从function.json读取默认值的逻辑\n- 支持两种device_id格式（MAC或IP）\n- 添加了错误追踪（traceback.print_exc()）\n\n#### 4. 代码质量改进\n- 修复了console.html中的typo（`dnrTemporal');n` → `dnrTemporal');`）\n- 移除了硬编码的\"1/60\"值\n- 添加了完整的错误处理\n\n### 当前状态\n服务已重启，应该运行着最新代码。刚刚添加了traceback调试信息来排查supported_levels问题。\n\n### 待验证\n需要在浏览器中测试：\n1. 连接设备后参数是否自动恢复\n2. 快门下拉菜单是否显示正确的支持值列表\n3. 修改参数后是否能正确应用到设备"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":4414,"output":970,"cacheRead":161108,"cacheWrite":262,"totalTokens":166754,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1783266227900,"responseId":"msg_52647bf5-2ae9-414c-a6df-eb49d47dd145"}}
