{"type":"message","id":"f684abec","parentId":"a59ea131","timestamp":"2026-07-05T16:34:02.350Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is right - I was stuck in a loop repeating the same message. Now I need to actually execute the task. Let me understand what the user wants:\n\n1. Backup current code (done)\n2. Fix the shutter supported_levels bug (the API returns only 2 values instead of 21 from function.json)\n3. Redesign the settings save/restore system:\n   - Save ALL settings from the console (except manual PTZ movement and current PTZ position)\n   - Save only once after whitebalance/focus search completes, not on every step\n   - Async, low overhead\n   - No new scripts, only modify existing files\n\nLet me now execute this step by step:\n\nStep 1: Backup - DONE\nStep 2: Fix shutter bug - need to fix the get_shutter function to read from function.json\nStep 3: Redesign settings save/restore\n\nFor the shutter bug, the code looks correct but the service wasn't restarted properly. Now all python processes are killed, so I can start fresh.\n\nFor the settings save/restore redesign:\n- Need to save ALL settings from the console (except PTZ movement/position)\n- Need to save asynchronously after WB/focus completes\n- Need to modify existing files only (router.py, device_settings.py, console.html, index.html, whitebalance.py, autofocus.py)\n\nLet me first fix the shutter bug by modifying router.py to properly read from function.json. Then I'll redesign the settings save/restore system.\n\nActually, looking at the current code in router.py for get_shutter:\n- It tries Method 1: DEVICES_DIR / device_id (where device_id might be IP or MAC)\n- If Method 1 fails (no function.json), it tries Method 2: iterate dirs and match by IP\n\nThe issue is that the service wasn't restarted. Now it's killed, so I can start fresh.\n\nBut wait - the user also wants me to redesign the settings save/restore system. Let me think about the approach