{"type":"message","id":"d858e980","parentId":"767a74fe","timestamp":"2026-07-05T16:55:35.227Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The shutter fix is now working! The API returns 21 values from function.json instead of the hardcoded 2 values. The `import json` fix resolved the issue.\n\nNow I need to move on to the main task the user requested:\n1. Save ALL settings as a snapshot per device (MAC-based)\n2. Save only once after WB/focus search completes\n3. Async, low overhead\n4. No new scripts\n\nLet me think about what the user wants:\n\n1. **Save ALL settings** - The user wants a complete snapshot of all console settings. Looking at the current `settings.json`, it already has: whitebalance, noisereduce, slow_shutter, exposure, iris, sharpness, image_settings. But the user wants ALL settings - that means I need to expand what's saved.\n\n2. **Save only once after WB/focus completes** - Currently, every PUT endpoint calls `save_device_settings()`. The user wants this removed for the search process. Instead, save only when the search finishes.\n\n3. **No new scripts** - Only modify existing files.\n\nLet me plan the changes:\n\n**What to save (complete snapshot):**\n- whitebalance (mode, red_gain, blue_gain) ✅ already saved\n- noisereduce (spatial, temporal) ✅ already saved\n- slow_shutter (dss_level, enabled) ✅ already saved\n- exposure (mode) ✅ already saved\n- shutter (level) ✅ already saved (after fix)\n- iris (level) ✅ already saved\n- sharpness (level) ✅ already saved\n- image_settings (brightness, contrast, saturation) ✅ already saved\n- What else? The user said \"除了手动PTZ运动控制，除了设备当前的PTZ位置，其他全都需要保存\"\n\nLooking at the console, other settings that can be changed:\n- OSD settings (info OSD on/off)\n- PTZ OSD switch\n- Stream settings (main/sub/third)\n- Live Stack settings\n- Tracking settings (sidereal/lunar)\n- Filter/day-night settings\n- Gain settings\n\nBut some of these are UI-only state, not device settings. Let me focus on the device image/visual settings that are actually sent to the camera.\n\nActually, re-reading the user's requirements:\n> 1. 我需要的，保存设备当前配置，是整个astrohub主控台上所有设置的快照，所有可以操作的设置，除了手动PTZ运动控制，除了设备当前的PTZ位置，其他全都需要保存\n\nSo ALL operable settings except:\n- Manual PTZ movement\n- Current PTZ position\n\nThis means I need to save ALL device settings that can be changed through the console. Let me check what endpoints exist for settings.\n\n> 2. 保存中，需要异步，需要降低占用，在画面控制-区域，也就是框选白平衡和框选自动对焦的时候，过程中有大量的调用，我需要在整个对焦或白平衡结束之后，执行一次保存，而不是每一步都保存\n\nSo the key change is:\n- Remove per-step saves during WB/focus search\n- Save once after the search completes\n- Make the save async\n\n> 3. 禁止开发新脚本，禁止引入新脚本，只允许在现有的条件下开发，禁止过度开发，需要全面修复。\n\nNo new files. Only modify existing ones.\n\nNow, looking at the current implementation:\n- Each PUT endpoint in router.py calls `save_device_settings()` after a successful PUT\n- This means during WB search (which calls the whitebalance gain endpoint multiple times), each step saves\n\nThe fix should be:\n1. Remove `save_device_settings()` calls from individual setter endpoints\n2. Add a new endpoint or mechanism to save all settings at once\n3. The frontend calls this endpoint once after WB/focus completes\n\nWait, but the user said \"禁止开发新脚本，禁止引入新脚本\". Does this mean I can't add new API endpoints? Or just new Python scripts?\n\nI think \"脚本\" means Python script files. Adding new API endpoints to existing router.py should be fine since it's modifying existing code, not creating new scripts.\n\nLet me plan the implementation:\n\n1. **Create a \"save all settings\" endpoint** in router.py that reads all current settings from the device and saves them to settings.json\n2. **Remove individual save calls** from setter endpoints (or keep them for manual changes but not during search)\n3. **Frontend calls save-all** after WB/focus search completes\n\nActually, wait. The user said \"过程中有大量的调用\". During WB/focus search, the search algorithm calls many endpoints. But looking at the whitebalance.py and autofocus.py, they call ISAPI directly, not through the router endpoints. So the router's save calls aren't triggered during the search.\n\nWait, let me re-check. The WB search in whitebalance.py calls `client.put(\"/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance\", xml_str)` directly on the ISAPI client. It doesn't go through the router. So the router's save calls aren't triggered.\n\nHmm, but the user said \"过程中有大量的调用\". Maybe the frontend is calling setter endpoints during the search? Let me check the SSE handlers in index.html...\n\nActually, looking at the code more carefully, the WB/focus search runs as a background task and sends SSE events. The frontend processes these events. But I don't see the frontend calling setter endpoints during the search.\n\nWait, maybe the issue is that the WB search itself saves settings at each step through the router? Let me check whitebalance.py...\n\nLooking at whitebalance.py, the search calls ISAPI directly:\n```python\nput_resp = client.put(\"/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance\", xml_str)\n```\n\nThis doesn't go through the router. So the router's save calls aren't triggered.\n\nBut wait, maybe the issue is different. Maybe the user wants the settings to be saved ONLY after the entire search completes, not during. Currently, if the user manually changes a setting (e.g., via the UI), it saves immediately. But during a WB search, the search changes settings many times. If each change triggers a save, that's wasteful.\n\nBut as I analyzed, the WB search doesn't go through the router. So the saves aren't triggered during the search.\n\nUnless... the frontend is calling the router endpoints during the search? Let me check the SSE event handlers...\n\nLooking at index.html, the SSE handler processes events like:\n```python\nyield {\"event\": \"whitebalance\", \"data\": json.dumps({\"type\": \"step\", \"step\": step, ...})}\n```\n\nThe frontend doesn't call any setter endpoints during the search. The search runs entirely on the backend.\n\nSo what's the problem? Maybe the user is seeing many saves because the frontend is polling or something?\n\nActually, I think I'm overcomplicating this. Let me re-read the user's requirements:\n\n> 2. 保存中，需要异步，需要降低占用，在画面控制-区域，也就是框选白平衡和框选自动对焦的时候，过程中有大量的调用，我需要在整个对焦或白平衡结束之后，执行一次保存，而不是每一步都保存\n\nThe user is saying that during WB/focus, there are many calls (the search algorithm makes many ISAPI calls to adjust R/B gain). After the search completes, they want ONE save of all settings, not a save at each step.\n\nSo the implementation should be:\n1. At the end of the WB search (in whitebalance.py), after the search completes, call a function to save all current settings\n2. At the end of the focus search (in autofocus.py), do the same\n3. Make these saves async (non-blocking)\n4. Remove the per-step saves if they exist\n\nBut wait, the WB/focus search doesn't save settings at each step currently. The saves only happen when the router endpoints are called.\n\nOK, I think the user might be confused, or maybe there's something I'm missing. Let me just implement what they want:\n\n1. A \"save all settings\" function that reads all current settings from the device and saves to settings.json\n2. Call this function once after WB/focus search completes\n3. Make it async\n\nAnd also, let me make sure the individual setter endpoints still save (for manual changes). Actually, the user said \"而不是每一步都保存\" - don't save at each step. So maybe I should remove the saves from individual setter endpoints and only save after search completes?\n\nBut that doesn't make sense either, because manual changes should still be saved.\n\nI think the correct interpretation is:\n- Manual changes: save immediately (current behavior)\n- WB/focus search: don't save at each step, save once after search completes\n\nSince the WB/focus search doesn't go through the router, the saves aren't triggered during the search. So the current behavior is already correct for manual changes.\n\nWhat I need to add is: after WB/focus search completes, save all current settings once.\n\nLet me implement this:\n\n1. Add a `save_all_settings()` function in device_settings.py that reads all current settings from the device and saves to settings.json\n2. Call this function at the end of WB search (in whitebalance.py) and focus search (in autofocus.py)\n3. Make it async\n\nFor reading all current settings from the device, I need to call the ISAPI endpoints:\n- `/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance` → mode, red_gain, blue_gain\n- `/Image/channels/1/noiseReduce` → spatial, temporal\n- `/Image/channels/1/Shutter` → level\n- `/Image/channels/1/Iris` → level\n- `/Image/channels/1/sharpness` → level\n- `/Image/channels/1/Exposure` → mode\n- `/Image/channels/1/DSS` → enabled, level\n- `/Image/channels/1` → brightness, contrast, saturation (actually this might be in a different endpoint)\n\nActually, for the \"save all\" function, I don't need to read from the device. I can just save the current values that are already known. But to get a complete snapshot, I should read from the device.\n\nWait, actually, the simplest approach is:\n1. Add a router endpoint `POST /ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all` that reads all current settings from the device and saves them\n2. The frontend calls this endpoint after WB/focus completes\n3. The backend reads all settings via ISAPI and saves to settings.json\n\nThis way:\n- No changes to individual setter endpoints\n- No changes to WB/focus search code\n- Just one new endpoint and one frontend call\n\nLet me implement this.\n\nActually, the user said \"禁止开发新脚本，禁止引入新脚本\". I think adding an endpoint to router.py is fine (it's modifying existing code). But I should not create new .py files.\n\nLet me plan:\n\n**router.py changes:**\n- Add `POST /ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all` endpoint\n- This endpoint reads all current settings from the device via ISAPI\n- Saves them to settings.json\n\n**console.html changes:**\n- After WB search completes (SSE done event), call the save-all endpoint\n- After focus search completes (SSE done event), call the save-all endpoint\n\n**device_settings.py changes:**\n- Add `save_all_settings_from_device(mac, device_ip)` function that reads all settings via ISAPI and saves\n\nWait, but device_settings.py shouldn't do ISAPI calls. It should just be a data layer. The ISAPI calls should be in router.py.\n\nLet me revise:\n\n**router.py changes:**\n- Add `POST /ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all` endpoint\n- This endpoint:\n  1. Gets the device controller\n  2. Reads all current settings via ISAPI\n  3. Calls `save_device_settings(mac, all_settings)` to save\n\n**console.html changes:**\n- After WB search completes, call `/api/v1/ptz/{ip}/image/settings-save-all`\n- After focus search completes, call `/api/v1/ptz/{ip}/image/settings-save-all`\n\nActually wait, I need to think about what settings to save. The user said \"所有可以操作的设置\". Let me list all the device settings that can be changed through the console:\n\n1. Exposure mode (manual/auto/IrisFirst/ShutterFirst)\n2. Shutter speed\n3. Iris level\n4. Gain level\n5. White balance mode (auto/manual/locked)\n6. White balance red gain\n7. White balance blue gain\n8. Noise reduce spatial level\n9. Noise reduce temporal level\n10. Sharpness level\n11. Slow shutter (DSS) enabled/level\n12. Brightness\n13. Contrast\n14. Saturation\n15. Filter (day/night)\n16. OSD on/off\n17. Stream settings\n\nThat's a lot. But many of these are already being saved individually. I just need to create a \"save all\" that reads them all at once.\n\nActually, I think the simplest approach is:\n1. The save-all endpoint reads all settings from the device\n2. Saves them all to settings.json\n3. Frontend calls this after WB/focus completes\n\nLet me also think about what the user means by \"异步\" (async). They want the save to not block the response. So the endpoint should return immediately and save in the background.\n\nIn Python/FastAPI, I can use `asyncio.create_task()` to run the save in the background.\n\nOK, let me now implement this. I'll:\n\n1. Add a `save_all_settings` endpoint in router.py\n2. The endpoint reads all settings from device via ISAPI\n3. Saves them to settings.json\n4. Returns immediately (async save)\n\n5. In console.html, call this endpoint after WB/focus completes\n\nActually, let me re-read the requirements one more time:\n\n> 2. 保存中，需要异步，需要降低占用，在画面控制-区域，也就是框选白平衡和框选自动对焦的时候，过程中有大量的调用，我需要在整个对焦或白平衡结束之后，执行一次保存，而不是每一步都保存\n\nOK so the key points are:\n1. Save should be async (non-blocking)\n2. Low overhead\n3. Save once after WB/focus completes, not at each step\n\n> 3. 禁止开发新脚本，禁止引入新脚本，只允许在现有的条件下开发，禁止过度开发，需要全面修复。\n\nNo new scripts. Only modify existing files.\n\nSo my plan is:\n1. Add `save_all` endpoint to router.py (modifying existing file)\n2. Modify console.html to call save_all after WB/focus completes\n\nLet me also make sure I'm not missing any settings. Let me check what the current settings.json has and what else should be added.\n\nCurrent settings.json:\n- whitebalance: mode, red_gain, blue_gain\n- noisereduce: spatial_level, temporal_level\n- slow_shutter: dss_level, enabled\n- exposure: mode\n- iris: level\n- sharpness: level\n- image_settings: brightness, contrast, saturation\n- last_updated\n\nWhat's missing:\n- shutter: level (this should be saved after the fix)\n- gain: level\n- filter: day/night mode\n- OSD settings\n\nActually, looking at the router.py, the shutter endpoint DOES call `save_device_settings` after a successful PUT. So shutter should be saved.\n\nBut the `settings.json` I saw earlier didn't have shutter. That's because the shutter set was failing (HTTP 400) before my fix. Now that the fix is in place, shutter saves should work.\n\nOK, let me now implement the save-all endpoint. I'll add it to router.py.\n\nActually, let me think about the simplest implementation:\n\n1. Add endpoint `POST /ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all`\n2. It reads all settings