should first announce the fix to the user and then proceed with the next task. The shutter bug is now fixed (21 values returned). Let me report this and then continue with the settings save redesign.\n\nLet me first report the fix, then start the settings save redesign.\n\nThe shutter fix:\n- Root cause: `import json` was missing from `get_shutter` and `set_shutter` functions\n- The `except Exception` was silently catching the `NameError: name 'json' is not defined`\n- This caused the function to fall back to the hardcoded min/max values\n- Fix: Added `import json` to both functions\n- Also deleted the rogue `192.168.5.72` directory that was interfering\n\nNow let me implement the settings save redesign.\n\nFor the save-all endpoint, I need to:\n1. Read all settings from the device via ISAPI\n2. Save them to settings.json\n3. Return immediately (async)\n\nLet me write the endpoint code.\n\nActually, I think I should use a subagent for this since it's a lot of code changes. But the user said \"禁止开发新脚本\" - no new scripts. I should do this myself.\n\nLet me plan the changes:\n\n**router.py:**\n- Add `POST /ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all` endpoint\n- This endpoint:\n  1. Gets the device MAC from device_id\n  2. Gets the ISAPI client\n  3. Reads all settings via ISAPI\n  4. Saves them to settings.json via `save_device_settings`\n  5. Returns success\n\n**console.html / index.html:**\n- After WB search completes, call the save-all endpoint\n- After focus search completes, call the save-all endpoint\n\nLet me start with router.py.\n\nActually, for reading all settings, I need to make multiple ISAPI calls. This could be slow. To make it async and non-blocking, I can:\n1. Return immediately from the endpoint\n2. Use `asyncio.create_task()` to run the save in the background\n\nBut I need to be careful about the ISAPI client - it might not be thread-safe.\n\nActually, FastAPI is async, so I can just make the endpoint async and await all the ISAPI calls. The endpoint will return after all calls complete, but it won't block other requests.\n\nFor truly async (fire-and-forget), I can use `asyncio.create_task()`. But then I need to handle errors properly.\n\nLet me just make it a regular async endpoint that does all the reads and saves, then returns. This is simple and correct.\n\nOK let me write the code now.\n\nFor reading settings, I'll need to call:\n- `/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance` → mode, redGain, blueGain\n- `/Image/channels/1/noiseReduce` → spatialLevel, temporalLevel (actually it might be FilteringType)\n- `/Image/channels/1/Shutter` → ShutterLevel\n- `/Image/channels/1/Iris` → irisLevel (or similar)\n- `/Image/channels/1/sharpness` → sharpnessLevel\n- `/Image/channels/1/Exposure` → exposureMode (wait, this might be different)\n- `/Image/channels/1/DSS` → enabled, DSSLevel\n- `/Image/channels/1` → brightness, contrast, saturation (in ImageAdjustment?)\n- `/Image/channels/1/gain` → gainLevel\n\nActually, I should look at the existing GET endpoints to see how they read settings. Let me check a few of them.\n\nActually, I think the simplest approach is to have the save-all endpoint call the internal functions that the GET endpoints use. But those functions return dicts, not ISAPI XML.\n\nOK, let me just write the endpoint that reads all settings via ISAPI and saves them. I'll base it on the existing GET endpoint logic.\n\nLet me write this now. I'll create the endpoint and the ISAPI reading code.\n\nActually, let me simplify. Instead of reading from ISAPI, I can have the endpoint accept a dict of settings to save. The frontend can collect all current settings from the UI and send them to the endpoint.\n\nBut that's less reliable because the UI might not have the latest values.\n\nOK, let me just do it the right way: read from ISAPI and save.\n\nLet me write the code.\n\nI'll add a function `_read_all_image_settings(mac, device_ip)` that reads all settings from the device and returns a dict. Then the save-all endpoint will call this function and save the result.\n\nLet me write this now. I need to be careful to not break any existing code.\n\nLet me start by announcing the shutter fix to the user, then implement the settings save redesign.\n\nActually, the user said \"继续\" (continue). So I should just continue working. Let me report the fix and then proceed with the settings save redesign.\n\nLet me report:\n- Shutter fix successful: 21 values now returned\n- Root cause: missing `import json`\n- Also deleted rogue directory\n\nThen proceed with settings save redesign:\n1. Add save-all endpoint to router.py\n2. Add frontend calls after WB/focus completes\n\nLet me write the save-all endpoint now.\n\nHere's my plan for the endpoint:\n\n```python\n@api_router.post(\"/ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all\", summary=\"保存所有设置快照\")\nasync def save_all_settings(device_id: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Read all current settings from device and save to settings.json. Async.\"\"\"\n    import json\n    import asyncio\n    \n    mgr = _managers.get(\"ptz_controller\")\n    if not mgr:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": \"PTZDeviceController未初始化\"}\n    \n    target_ip = _resolve_device_id_to_ip(mgr, device_id)\n    if not target_ip:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"无法解析设备标识: {device_id}\"}\n    \n    ctrl, err = mgr._get_controller(target_ip)\n    if err:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": err}\n    \n    client = ctrl.client\n    mac_clean = device_id.replace(\":\", \"\").replace(\"-\", \"\").lower()\n    if len(mac_clean) != 12:\n        # Try to find MAC from info.json\n        for device_dir in DEVICES_DIR.iterdir():\n            if device_dir.is_dir():\n                info_file = device_dir / \"info.json\"\n                if info_file.exists():\n                    try:\n                        info = json.loads(info_file.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n                        if info.get(\"ip\") == target_ip:\n                            mac_clean = device_dir.name\n                            break\n                    except Exception:\n                        continue\n    \n    if len(mac_clean) != 12:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": \"无法获取设备MAC\"}\n    \n    settings = {}\n    \n    # Read white balance\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            wb = {\"mode\": \"auto\"}\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag == \"whiteBalanceMode\":\n                    wb[\"mode\"] = elem.text or \"auto\"\n                elif tag == \"whiteBalanceRed\":\n                    wb[\"red_gain\"] = int(elem.text or 0)\n                elif tag == \"whiteBalanceBlue\":\n                    wb[\"blue_gain\"] = int(elem.text or 0)\n            settings[\"whitebalance\"] = wb\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read noise reduce\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/noiseReduce\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            nr = {}\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag in (\"spatialLevel\", \"DnrSpatialLevel\"):\n                    nr[\"spatial_level\"] = int(elem.text or 0)\n                elif tag in (\"temporalLevel\", \"DnrTemporalLevel\"):\n                    nr[\"temporal_level\"] = int(elem.text or 0)\n            if nr:\n                settings[\"noisereduce\"] = nr\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read shutter\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/Shutter\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag in (\"ShutterLevel\", \"shutterLevel\"):\n                    settings[\"shutter\"] = {\"level\": elem.text or \"1/30000\"}\n                    break\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read iris\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/Iris\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag in (\"irisLevel\", \"IrisLevel\", \"currentIrisLevel\"):\n                    settings[\"iris\"] = {\"level\": int(elem.text or 0)}\n                    break\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read sharpness\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/sharpness\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag in (\"sharpnessLevel\", \"SharpnessLevel\"):\n                    settings[\"sharpness\"] = {\"level\": int(elem.text or 0)}\n                    break\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read exposure\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/Exposure\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag == \"exposureMode\":\n                    settings[\"exposure\"] = {\"mode\": elem.text or \"auto\"}\n                    break\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read DSS\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/DSS\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            dss = {}\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag == \"enabled\":\n                    dss[\"enabled\"] = elem.text == \"true\"\n                elif tag == \"DSSLevel\":\n                    dss[\"dss_level\"] = elem.text or \"off\"\n            if dss:\n                settings[\"slow_shutter\"] = dss\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read image settings (brightness, contrast, saturation)\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            img = {}\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag == \"brightnessLevel\":\n                    img[\"brightness\"] = int(elem.text or 50)\n                elif tag == \"contrastLevel\":\n                    img[\"contrast\"] = int(elem.text or 50)\n                elif tag == \"saturationLevel\":\n                    img[\"saturation\"] = int(elem.text or 50)\n            if img:\n                settings[\"image_settings\"] = img\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read gain\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/gain\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag in (\"gainLevel\", \"currentGainLevel\"):\n                    settings[\"gain\"] = {\"level\": int(elem.text or 0)}\n                    break\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Save\n    try:\n        save_device_settings(mac_clean, settings)\n        return {\"success\": True, \"message\": f\"已保存 {len(settings)} 项设置\", \"saved_keys\": list(settings.keys())}\n    except Exception as e:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"保存失败: {e}\"}\n```\n\nThis is a lot of code. Let me simplify it. Actually, I realize I should look at the existing GET endpoints to see exactly what XML tags they parse, to make sure I'm using the right tag names.\n\nLet me read a few of the GET endpoints to understand the XML structure.\n\nActually, this is getting very long. Let me just write the endpoint code and test it. I'll base the XML parsing on the existing GET endpoints.\n\nLet me first announce the shutter fix, then implement the save-all endpoint.\n\nWait, I should also consider: the user said \"禁止过度开发\". Maybe I should keep it simple. Instead of reading all settings via ISAPI, I can just have the frontend send all current settings to the save-all endpoint. This avoids the ISAPI reads.\n\nBut that's less reliable because the UI might not have the latest values.\n\nOK, let me just implement it properly with ISAPI reads. Let me look at the existing GET endpoints to understand the XML structure.\n\nActually, let me just write the code based on what I know. I can test it and fix any issues.\n\nLet me also think about the frontend changes. After WB/focus completes, the frontend should call the save-all endpoint. Let me check the SSE handlers in index.html to see where the WB/focus completion is handled.\n\nActually, looking at the code, the WB/focus search is triggered from console.html, and the SSE events are handled in index.html. The completion is signaled by a \"done\" or \"catch\" event.\n\nLet me add the save-all call in the SSE handler after the \"done\" event.\n\nOK, let me now implement this. I'll:\n1. Announce the shutter fix\n2. Add the save-all endpoint to router.py\n3. Add the frontend call in index.html\n\nLet me start coding.\n快门bug已修复！原因：`get_shutter` 和 `set_shutter` 函数缺少 `import json`，导致 `NameError` 被静默捕获，回退到硬编码的 min/max 值。\n\n现在返回正确的21个值：`['1/25', '1/50', '1/75', ..., '1/10000', '1/30000']`\n\n现在继续实现设置保存系统的重新设计。先了解当前前端如何处理WB/对焦完成事件：\n...\nThe shutter bug is fixed. The root cause was that `get_shutter` and `set_shutter` functions were missing `import json`. The `NameError` was silently caught by the `except Exception` clause, causing the function to fall back to the hardcoded min/max values.\n\nNow the API correctly returns 21 values from function.json: `['1/25', '1/50', '1/75', ..., '1/10000', '1/30000']`\n\nNow I need to continue with the settings save system redesign. Let me understand how the frontend handles WB/focus completion events.\n快门bug修复完成。现在继续实现设置保存系统重新设计。检查前端WB/对焦完成事件处理：\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_344fd6fe8d524022b177c941","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nwith open('astrohub/src/web/includes/index.html', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Find WB done event handler\nidx = content.find('whitebalance')\nif idx > 0:\n    # Print context around WB SSE handling\n    start = max(0, idx - 200)\n    end = min(len(content), idx + 500)\n    print(content[start:end])\n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_0e407c85ed7b4f04b830ad67","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nwith open('astrohub/src/web/includes/console.html', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Find WB/focus done event handling\nfor keyword in ['done', 'catch', 'complete', '结束', '完成']:\n    idx = content.find(keyword)\n    if idx > 0:\n        start = max(0, idx - 100)\n        end = min(len(content), idx + 200)\n        print(f'--- Found \\\"{keyword}\\\" at {idx} ---')\n        print(content[start:end])\n        print()\n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n</think>\n\nThe user wants me to continue. The shutter fix is now working - it returns 21 values from function.json! Now I need to move on to the main task the user requested:\n\n1. Save ALL settings as a snapshot per device (not just individual settings)\n2. Save only once after WB/focus completes, not during each step\n3. Async, low overhead\n4. No new scripts - only modify existing code\n\nLet me first verify the shutter fix is complete by testing setting a value from the new list, then move on to the main task.\n\nThe main task is to redesign the settings save/restore system:\n- Currently, each setter endpoint saves immediately after PUT\n- User wants: save only once after WB/focus search completes\n- Save ALL settings as a snapshot\n- Async, low overhead\n\nI need to:\n1. Remove individual saves from each setter endpoint\n2. Add a \"save all settings\" endpoint\n3. Call it only after WB/focus completes\n4. Make it async\n\nLet me first test the shutter setting works with the new values, then proceed with the main task.\n**✅ 快门bug修复成功！** API现在返回21个正确的值（从function.json读取），包含1/600，不包含错误的1/60。\n\n现在测试设置快门是否成功：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_be01f3ab85d940e1a5339379","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"import requests,json; r=requests.post('http://localhost:10280/api/v1/ptz/192.168.5.72/image/shutter', json={'level':'1/600'}); print(r.json())\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_d13a29130bdf4183b777469d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"import requests,json; r=requests.get('http://localhost:10280/api/v1/ptz/192.168.5.72/image/shutter'); print('current:', r.json()['data']['current_level'])\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_70acc5fddcf643e1a6284057","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"import requests,json; r=requests.post('http://localhost:10280/api/v1/ptz/192.168.5.72/image/shutter', json={'level':'1/250'}); print(r.json()); import time; time.sleep(1); r2=requests.get('http://localhost:10280/api/v1/ptz/192.168.5.72/image/shutter'); print('after:', r2.json()['data']['current_level'])\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_d16b6ae85d48452da2e4a852","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"import reques