{"type":"message","id":"bf28fced","parentId":"9af5791d","timestamp":"2026-07-05T16:57:14.073Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to continue the task. Let me analyze what I've learned from the tool results:\n\n1. **Shutter fix is working**: The API now returns 21 values correctly from function.json\n2. **Shutter set is working**: Setting 1/250 works and the device reflects the change\n3. **Settings saved**: The settings.json now has shutter: 1/600 saved after the first set call\n\nNow I need to understand the user's requirements again:\n\n1. **Save ALL settings** - not just individual ones, but a complete snapshot of ALL console settings (except manual PTZ movement and current PTZ position)\n2. **Async save** - save once after WB/focus completes, not during every step\n3. **No new scripts** - only modify existing files\n4. **Low overhead** - async, non-blocking\n\nThe current implementation:\n- Each setter endpoint in router.py calls `save_device_settings()` after a successful PUT\n- This means during WB/focus search (which makes many ISAPI calls), there are many saves\n- The user wants: save once AFTER the search completes\n\nLooking at the tool results:\n- index.html doesn't exist at `astrohub/src/web/includes/index.html` - it might be at a different path\n- settings.json now has shutter saved (1/600) after the first set call\n\nI need to:\n1. Find where the WB/focus search completion is handled\n2. Remove individual save calls from setter endpoints\n3. Add a \"save all settings\" function that reads ALL current settings and saves them as a snapshot\n4. Call this function only after WB/focus completes\n\nBut wait - the user said \"禁止开发新脚本，禁止引入新脚本，只允许在现有的条件下开发\". So I can't create new files. I need to modify existing ones.\n\nLet me think about the architecture:\n- The WB/focus search is in `src/advanced/whitebalance.py` and `src/advanced/autofocus.py`\n- The search completes and sends a \"done\" event via SSE\n- The frontend (console.html/index.html) handles the \"done\" event\n\nThe approach should be:\n1. Remove individual `save_device_settings()` calls from router.py setter endpoints\n2. Add a new endpoint in router.py: `POST /ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all` that reads ALL current settings from the device and saves them\n3. In the frontend, after WB/focus completes, call this new endpoint once\n\nBut wait - the user said \"禁止过度开发\". Maybe I should keep it simpler:\n- Keep the individual saves for manual changes\n- But remove saves during WB/focus search\n- Add a single save after WB/focus completes\n\nActually, re-reading the requirements:\n> \"保存中，需要异步，需要降低占用，在画面控制-区域，也就是框选白平衡和框选自动对焦的时候，过程中有大量的调用，我需要在整个对焦或白平衡结束之后，执行一次保存，而不是每一步都保存\"\n\nSo the issue is: during WB/focus search, there are many API calls (setShutter, setIris, setWhiteBalance, etc.), and each one triggers a save. The user wants ONE save after the entire search completes.\n\nThe approach:\n1. Add a flag/mechanism to suppress saves during WB/focus search\n2. After search completes, call save-all once\n\nBut this is complex. A simpler approach:\n1. Remove individual saves from setter endpoints\n2. Add a \"save all\" endpoint\n3. Frontend calls \"save all\" after WB/focus completes\n\nBut the user said \"禁止过度开发\". Let me think about what's minimal:\n\nOption A: Keep individual saves but add a debounce/batch mechanism\nOption B: Remove individual saves, add \"save all\" endpoint, call it from frontend\nOption C: Keep individual saves but suppress them during search\n\nI think Option B is cleanest but requires modifying frontend. Option C is simpler but requires state management.\n\nActually, looking at the current code more carefully, the WB/focus search uses ISAPI directly, not the router endpoints. So the router saves aren't triggered during search. Let me verify this.\n\nLooking at the whitebalance.py and autofocus.py code from the context:\n- They use `client.put()` directly, not the router endpoints\n- So the router's `save_device_settings()` calls aren't triggered during search\n\nSo what's the actual problem? Maybe the user is referring to the frontend making many calls? Or maybe the search is using the router endpoints?\n\nLet me re-read the context... The whitebalance.py uses `client.put(\"/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance\", xml_str)` directly. This bypasses the router, so `save_device_settings()` is not called.\n\nSo the current behavior is:\n- Manual changes via UI → router endpoint → save\n- WB/focus search → ISAPI direct → no save\n\nAfter search completes, nothing is saved. The user wants ONE save after search completes.\n\nSo I need to:\n1. Add a \"save all settings\" endpoint\n2. Call it from frontend after WB/focus completes\n\nBut wait, the user said \"保存设备当前配置，是整个astrohub主控台上所有设置的快照\". This means I need to save ALL settings, not just the ones that were changed during search.\n\nSo the \"save all\" endpoint needs to:\n1. Read ALL current settings from the device via ISAPI\n2. Save them all to settings.json\n\nThis is more complex. Let me think about what settings to save:\n- whitebalance (mode, red_gain, blue_gain)\n- noisereduce (spatial, temporal)\n- slow_shutter (dss_level, enabled)\n- exposure (mode)\n- shutter (level)\n- iris (level)\n- sharpness (level)\n- image_settings (brightness, contrast, saturation)\n- gain (level)\n- OSD settings\n- stream settings\n- etc.\n\nBut reading all of these from the device requires many ISAPI calls, which is slow and puts load on the device.\n\nA simpler approach: just save what's in `deviceImageParams` on the frontend. The frontend already has all the current settings from `loadAllImageParams()`. So the frontend can send all these values to the save endpoint.\n\nBut the user said \"禁止过度开发\". Let me think about what's truly necessary.\n\nActually, I think the simplest approach is:\n1. Add a new endpoint: `POST /ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all`\n2. This endpoint accepts a dict of all settings\n3. The frontend sends this dict after WB/focus completes\n4. The endpoint saves it to settings.json\n\nThis avoids reading from the device (which is slow) and just saves what the frontend knows.\n\nBut wait, the frontend might not have ALL settings. It only has what was loaded via `loadAllImageParams()`. Some settings like OSD, stream, etc. might not be in there.\n\nOK, let me take a step back. The user said:\n- \"保存设备当前配置，是整个astrohub主控台上所有设置的快照\"\n- \"所有可以操作的设置，除了手动PTZ运动控制，除了设备当前的PTZ位置\"\n\nSo I need to save everything. The simplest way is to read from the device.\n\nBut reading from the device is slow. Let me think about the performance:\n- Each ISAPI call takes ~20-50ms\n- There are ~10 different settings to read\n- Total: ~200-500ms\n\nThis is acceptable for a \"save all\" operation that happens once after WB/focus completes.\n\nOK, let me implement:\n1. A new endpoint in router.py: `POST /ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all`\n2. This endpoint reads ALL settings from the device via ISAPI\n3. Saves them to settings.json\n4. Called from frontend after WB/focus completes\n\nBut the user said \"禁止开发新脚本\". Does a new endpoint count as a new script? I think not - it's modifying existing router.py.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the requirements:\n> \"禁止开发新脚本，禁止引入新脚本，只允许在现有的条件下开发\"\n\nThis means no new .py files. Modifying existing router.py is fine.\n\nOK, let me also think about the async part:\n> \"保存中，需要异步，需要降低占用\"\n\nThis means the save should not block the main thread. In FastAPI, all endpoints are async by default. So I can just make the endpoint async and use `await` for ISAPI calls.\n\nBut actually, the ISAPI calls are synchronous (using requests). To make them async, I'd need to use `asyncio.to_thread()` or `run_in_executor()`. Or I can just make the endpoint fast enough that it doesn't block.\n\nActually, looking at the current code, the ISAPI calls are synchronous but FastAPI runs them in a thread pool. So they're already async from the frontend's perspective.\n\nOK, let me just implement the endpoint and test it.\n\nPlan:\n1. Add `POST /ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all` endpoint to router.py\n2. This endpoint reads all settings from device and saves to settings.json\n3. Add frontend call to this endpoint after WB/focus completes\n\nLet me also check what the frontend currently does after WB/focus completes. I need to find where the \"done\" event is handled.\n\nFrom the context, the frontend handles SSE events for WB/focus. The \"done\" event triggers some cleanup. I need to add a call to the save-all endpoint there.\n\nLet me start implementing.\n\nActually, I realize I need to be more careful. The user said \"整个过程\" (the whole process). During WB/focus, the search algorithm makes many changes to device settings. After it completes, we want to save the FINAL state.\n\nSo the save-all endpoint should:\n1. Read ALL current settings from device\n2. Save to settings.json\n\nThis is straightforward.\n\nLet me also think about what \"ALL settings\" means. Looking at the router.py endpoints, the settings are:\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/exposure` - exposure mode\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/shutter` - shutter level\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/iris` - iris level\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/whitebalance` - WB mode, red gain, blue gain\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/noisereduce` - spatial, temporal\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/sharpness` - sharpness level\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/color` - brightness, contrast, saturation\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/gain` - gain level\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/slow-shutter` - DSS enabled, level\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/filter` - day/night filter\n\nAnd possibly:\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/osd/ptz` - PTZ OSD\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/osd/info` - Info OSD\n- Stream settings\n\nBut OSD and stream settings might not be relevant. Let me focus on image settings first.\n\nOK, let me implement the endpoint. I'll read all these settings from the device and save them.\n\nActually, I just realized something. The current `save_device_settings()` in router.py is called after each individual PUT. This means:\n- When user changes whitebalance mode → save whitebalance\n- When user changes shutter → save shutter\n- etc.\n\nSo settings.json accumulates all settings over time. But it might not have ALL settings if the user hasn't changed them all.\n\nThe new \"save all\" endpoint should read ALL settings from the device and save them, ensuring a complete snapshot.\n\nLet me implement this now.\n\nActually, I should also consider: should I remove the individual saves from the setter endpoints? The user said \"而不是每一步都保存\" (not save at every step). This suggests they want to remove individual saves and only save after the entire process.\n\nBut that would break manual changes. If the user manually changes a setting, they'd expect it to be saved.\n\nWait, re-reading the requirement:\n> \"在画面控制-区域，也就是框选白平衡和框选自动对焦的时候，过程中有大量的调用，我需要在整个对焦或白平衡结束之后，执行一次保存，而不是每一步都保存\"\n\nThis specifically refers to WB/focus search. During the search, there are many calls. The user wants ONE save after the search completes.\n\nSo the approach is:\n1. Keep individual saves for manual changes (via UI)\n2. But during WB/focus search, suppress saves\n3. After search completes, save all once\n\nHow to suppress saves during search? Options:\n- Add a flag in the backend (e.g., `_suppress_saves = True` during search)\n- Or remove individual saves and rely on frontend to call save-all\n\nI think the cleanest approach is:\n- Remove individual saves from setter endpoints\n- Add save-all endpoint\n- Frontend calls save-all after any change (manual or after WB/focus)\n\nBut this might be too aggressive. Let me think...\n\nActually, the simplest approach that meets the requirement:\n1. Keep individual saves in router.py (they're fast and only save what changed)\n2. After WB/focus completes, call save-all to ensure everything is saved\n\nThis way:\n- Manual changes are saved immediately\n- WB/focus search saves happen incrementally (which is fine)\n- After search, one final save-all ensures everything is captured\n\nWait, but the user said \"而不是每一步都保存\". They don't want saves at every step. So I should remove individual saves during search.\n\nHmm, but the search uses ISAPI directly, not the router endpoints. So individual saves aren't triggered during search anyway.\n\nLet me verify this by looking at the whitebalance.py code from the context... Yes, it uses `client.put()` directly, bypassing the router. So no saves during search.\n\nSo the current behavior is:\n- Manual changes → router → save\n- WB/focus search → ISAPI direct → no save\n\nAfter search, nothing is saved. The user wants ONE save after search.\n\nSo I just need to:\n1. Add save-all endpoint\n2. Call it from frontend after WB/focus completes\n\nThis is simpler than I thought.\n\nBut wait, the user also said \"保存设备当前配置，是整个astrohub主控台上所有设置的快照\". This means the save-all should save ALL settings, not just the ones that were changed during search.\n\nSo the save-all endpoint needs to read all settings from device and save them.\n\nOK, let me implement this now. I'll:\n1. Add a new endpoint in router.py\n2. It reads all settings from device\n3. Saves to settings.json\n4. Frontend calls it after WB/focus completes\n\nLet me also make it async by using `asyncio.to_thread()` for the ISAPI calls.\n\nActually, I realize I'm overthinking this. Let me just implement it step by step.\n\nStep 1: Add save-all endpoint to router.py\nStep 2: Test it\nStep 3: Add frontend call after WB/focus completes\n\nLet me start.\n老板，快门修复成功！测试验证：\n- ✅ 获取返回21个值（从function.json读取）\n- ✅ 设置1/600成功\n- ✅ 设置1/250成功并确认设备已更新\n- ✅ settings.json已保存shutter\n\n现在继续实现设置保存系统重新设计。先了解前端WB/对焦完成事件处理位置：\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_6c653ed001384262a5188110","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Path astrohub\\src\\web -Recurse -Filter \"*.html\" | Select-Object FullName","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-facto