{"type":"message","id":"7a76953f","parentId":"c25bf14c","timestamp":"2026-07-05T17:04:23.323Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The file is 3106 lines. The byte offset 151169 corresponds to around line 2795 based on my calculation. But that doesn't seem right - the WB/focus search code should be somewhere else. Let me search more specifically for the whitebalance/focus SSE handling code.\n\nActually, looking at the find_wb_focus.py output, I can see the code around position 151169:\n```\nvar endpoint = mode === 'whitebalance' ? '/api/v1/vision/whitebalance-search'\n                                       : '/api/v1/vision/focus-search';\nvar label = mode === 'whitebalance' ? '白平衡' : '对焦';\n```\n\nThis is in the function that starts the WB/focus search. I need to find where this function handles the response.\n\nLet me search for the function that contains this code and see how it handles the response. I need to look for fetch or XMLHttpRequest calls related to the vision search endpoints.\n\nLet me search more specifically for the SSE handling code. The search might use fetch with a ReadableStream to process SSE events. Let me find the complete function.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"文件3106行。需要找到WB/focus搜索的完整处理函数。让我直接搜索相关代码：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_9eea4a36ef0049eeb0db3aa6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory && python -c \"\nwith open('astrohub/src/web/index.html', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Find the complete WB/focus search function\nidx = content.find('vision/whitebalance-search')\nif idx >= 0:\n    # Find function start\n    func_start = content.rfind('function ', 0, idx)\n    # Find function end (next function or closing brace pattern)\n    # Look for the next function definition or end of script\n    func_end = content.find('\\n    function ', idx + 1)\n    if func_end < 0:\n        func_end = content.find('\