{"type":"message","id":"e1b2ff9d","parentId":"443fd12f","timestamp":"2026-07-05T17:05:56.252Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the complete picture of the WB/focus search function. The SSE event handling is in the `_finishRegion()` function in index.html. When the search completes (`ev.type === 'done'`), it updates the UI but doesn't save settings.\n\nThe user's requirements:\n1. Save ALL settings after WB/focus completes\n2. Async, low overhead\n3. No new scripts\n4. No over-engineering\n\nThe simplest approach:\n1. Add a new endpoint in router.py: `POST /ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all`\n2. In the frontend `_finishRegion()` function, after `ev.type === 'done'`, call this endpoint once\n\n\n3. The endpoint should read all current settings from the device and save them to settings.json\n\nLet me check what settings are available in the router to understand what I need to save.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"完美！找到了SSE处理逻辑。现在看到`ev.type === 'done'`就是WB/对焦完成的回调位置。\n\n现在执行用户要求的设置保存重新设计：\n\n1. **后端**：在router.py添加一个保存所有设置的端点\n2. **前端**：在`ev.type === 'done'`处调用该端点\n\n先查看router.py中现有的保存逻辑：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_1229739bed854ab6a172346b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory && python -c \"\nwith open('astrohub/src/api/router.py', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Find save_device_settings function\nidx = content.find('save_device_settings')\npositions = []\nwhile idx >= 0:\n    positions.append(idx)\n    idx = content.find('save_device_settings', idx + 1)\n\nprint(f'Found save_device_settings at {len(positions)} positions')\nfor pos in positions[:10]:\n    start = max(0, pos - 50)\n    end = min(len(content), pos + 200)\n    print(f'  pos {pos}: ...{content[start:end]}...')\n    print()\n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-