{"type":"message","id":"6769b530","parentId":"9827becf","timestamp":"2026-07-05T17:06:48.044Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to continue with the task. I've found the WB/focus search completion handler in index.html. The `ev.type === 'done'` is where the search completes successfully.\n\nNow I understand the architecture:\n1. `save_device_settings` is called in each setter endpoint in router.py\n2. The user wants to:\n   - Save ALL settings as a snapshot\n   - Save asynchronously\n   - Save only once after WB/focus completes\n   - Not save on every step during WB/focus search\n\nThe approach:\n1. Create a new endpoint in router.py: `POST /api/v1/ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all` that reads all current settings from the device and saves them as a snapshot\n2. In the frontend `_finishRegion()` function, after `ev.type === 'done'`, call this new endpoint once\n3. The endpoint should be async (return immediately, save in background)\n\nBut the user said \"禁止开发新脚本\" (no new scripts). So I should modify existing files only, not create new ones.\n\nLooking at the current code:\n- Each setter endpoint calls `save_device_settings()` to save individual settings\n- The user wants to save ALL settings as a snapshot after WB/focus completes\n- The user also said \"而不是每一步都保存\" (not save on every step)\n\nThe WB/focus search process makes many API calls to adjust settings. Currently, each call saves the settings. The user wants to:\n1. NOT save during the search process (remove saves from setter endpoints? or suppress them?)\n2. Save once after the search completes\n\nActually, re-reading the requirements:\n- \"保存中，需要异步，需要降低占用\" - save should be async, low overhead\n- \"在画面控制-区域，也就是框选白平衡和框选自动对焦的时候，过程中有大量的调用\" - during WB/focus, there are many calls\n- \"我需要在整个对焦或白平衡结束之后，执行一次保存\" - need to save once after WB/focus completes\n- \"而不是每一步都保存\" - not save on every step\n\nSo the approach is:\n1. During WB/focus search, the backend makes many ISAPI calls. These should NOT trigger individual saves.\n2. After WB/focus completes, save ALL settings once.\n\nLooking at the code, the WB/focus search is done via `/api/v1/vision/whitebalance-search` and `/api/v1/vision/focus-search`. These are SSE endpoints that run the search algorithm. The search algorithm makes ISAPI calls directly, not through the router endpoints.\n\nSo the issue is: the search algorithm changes device settings via ISAPI, but these changes are NOT saved to settings.json. The user wants to save ALL settings after the search completes.\n\nThe solution:\n1. After WB/focus completes (in the SSE done handler), call a new endpoint to save all current settings from the device\n2. This endpoint reads all current settings from the device via ISAPI and saves them to settings.json\n\nLet me check the existing `save_device_settings` function to understand its signature. It takes a MAC address and a settings dict.\n\nActually, I need to create a function that:\n1. Reads all current settings from the device via ISAPI\n2. Saves them all to settings.json in one call\n\nLet me check what settings are available and how to read them.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the code:\n- `save_device_settings(mac, settings_dict)` saves the settings_dict to the device's settings.json\n- Each setter endpoint reads current settings from ISAPI, updates the device, then saves to settings.json\n\nThe user wants:\n1. A single endpoint that reads ALL current settings from the device and saves them\n2. Called after WB/focus completes\n\nLet me create this endpoint in router.py and call it from the frontend after WB/focus completes.\n\nActually, wait. The user said \"禁止开发新脚本，禁止引入新脚本，只允许在现有的条件下开发\". This means no new files, only modify existing ones.\n\nSo I need to:\n1. Add a new endpoint in router.py (modifying existing file, OK)\n2. Add a call to this endpoint in the frontend after WB/focus completes (modifying existing file, OK)\n\nThe endpoint should:\n1. Read all current settings from the device via ISAPI\n2. Save them all to settings.json\n\nLet me look at what settings are available and how to read them. I need to check the device's ISAPI endpoints.\n\nActually, I think the simplest approach is:\n1. Add a new endpoint `POST /api/v1/ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all` in router.py\n2. This endpoint reads all current settings from the device via ISAPI (whitebalance, noisereduce, exposure, shutter, iris, sharpness, slow_shutter, image_settings)\n3. Saves them all to settings.json in one call\n4. In the frontend `_finishRegion()` function, after `ev.type === 'done'`, call this endpoint\n\nLet me implement this.\n\nFirst, let me check what the current settings.json structure looks like and what the save_device_settings function expects.\n找到9处调用点。现在理解需求：\n\n**当前问题**：每个setter端点都调用`save_device_settings`保存单个设置。WB/对焦搜索过程中会调用很多setter，导致频繁保存。\n\n**解决方案**：\n1. 添加新端点`POST /api/v1/ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all` - 异步保存所有当前设置\n2. 前端在`ev.type === 'done'`处调用该端点\n3. 移除setter端点中的`save_device_settings`调用（可选，取决于需求）\n\n先查看save_device_settings的签名和现有设置结构：\n...\nThe user wants me to continue. I've found the 9 call sites for save_device_settings in router.py. Now I understand the architecture:\n\n1. `save_device_settings` is called in each setter endpoint to save individual settings\n2. The WB/focus search process makes many API calls to adjust settings\n3. The user wants to:\n   - Save ALL settings as a snapshot\n   - Save asynchronously (non-blocking)\n   - Save only once after WB/focus completes\n   - Not save on every step during WB/focus search\n\nThe solution:\n1. Add a new endpoint `POST /api/v1/ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all` in router.py that reads all current settings from the device and saves them all at once\n2. Make it async (return immediately, save in background)\n3. Call this endpoint from the frontend after `ev.type === 'done'` in the WB/focus SSE handler\n\nLet me first check what settings are currently being saved and how to read all current settings from the device.\n\nActually, looking at the code more carefully:\n- Each setter endpoint (whitebalance, noisereduce, exposure, shutter, iris, sharpness, slow_shutter, image_settings) calls `save_device_settings` with a partial dict\n- The settings.json file accumulates these partial updates\n\nFor the \"save all\" endpoint, I need to:\n1. Read the current settings from the device via ISAPI (or from the existing settings.json)\n2. Save them all at once\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to just read the current settings.json and re-save it with a fresh timestamp. Or better, read all current settings from the device and save them.\n\nBut wait, the user said \"禁止开发新脚本，禁止引入新脚本\" - no new scripts. So I should modify existing files only.\n\nLet me think about the minimal change:\n1. Add a new endpoint in router.py that saves all settings (reads from device and saves to settings.json)\n2. Call this endpoint from the frontend after WB/focus completes\n\nActually, re-reading the requirements:\n- \"保存设备当前配置，是整个astrohub主控台上所有设置的快照\" - save ALL settings as a snapshot\n- \"保存中，需要异步，需要降低占用\" - async, low overhead\n- \"在画面控制-区域，也就是框选白平衡和框选自动对焦的时候，过程中有大量的调用，我需要在整个对焦或白平衡结束之后，执行一次保存\" - save once after WB/focus completes, not on every step\n- \"禁止开发新脚本，禁止引入新脚本，只允许在现有的条件下开发\" - no new scripts, only modify existing files\n- \"禁止过度开发，需要全面修复\" - no over-engineering, fix comprehensively\n\nSo the plan is:\n1. Add a new endpoint in router.py that saves all current settings from the device\n2. Modify the frontend to call this endpoint after WB/focus completes\n3. Optionally remove the individual save calls from setter endpoints (or keep them for manual changes)\n\nActually, I think the best approach is:\n1. Keep the individual save calls in setter endpoints for manual changes\n2. Add a \"save all\" endpoint\n3. Call \"save all\" after WB/focus completes\n\nBut the user said \"而不是每一步都保存\" - not save on every step. This suggests removing the individual save calls from the WB/focus search process.\n\nWait, the WB/focus search doesn't call the setter endpoints. It directly calls ISAPI. So the individual saves in setter endpoints are not triggered during WB/focus search.\n\nSo the issue is different. Let me re-read the requirements:\n- \"保存设备当前配置，是整个astrohub主控台上所有设置的快照\" - save ALL settings as a snapshot\n- \"保存中，需要异步，需要降低占用\" - async, low overhead\n- \"在画面控制-区域，也就是框选白平衡和框选自动对焦的时候，过程中有大量的调用，我需要在整个对焦或白平衡结束之后，执行一次保存\" - save once after WB/focus completes\n\nI think the user wants:\n1. A way to save ALL current settings from the device (not just individual settings)\n2. This save should happen once after WB/focus completes\n3. The save should be async\n\nSo the solution is:\n1. Add a new endpoint that reads all current settings from the device and saves them\n2. Call this endpoint from the frontend after WB/focus completes\n\nLet me implement this.\n\nFirst, let me check what settings are available and how to read them all. I need to look at the existing GET endpoints to see what settings can be read.\n\nActually, I think the simplest approach is to just save the current state of all settings. The settings.json file already has a structure. I just need to ensure all settings are saved at once after WB/focus completes.\n\nLet me add a new endpoint in router.py:\n- `POST /api/v1/ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all`\n- This endpoint reads all current settings from the device and saves them to settings.json\n\nThen modify the frontend to call this endpoint after `ev.type === 'done'`.\n\nLet me start implementing.\n明白。现在需要：\n1. 查看save_device_settings的签名\n2. 添加新端点保存所有设置\n3. 修改前端调用\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_61ccafaab9144c5b9484cd6c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory && python -c \"\nwith open('astrohub/src/advanced/device_settings.py', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Find save_settings function\nidx = content.find('def save_settings')\nif idx >= 0:\n    print(content[idx:idx+500])\n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":674,"output":2537,"cacheRead":16929,"cacheWrite":37034,"totalTokens":57174,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783271156924,"responseId":"msg_d3621eb5-d421-4a35-9480-cb2157730658"}}
{"type":"message","id":"48539a4f","parentId":"6769b530","timestamp":"2026-07-05T17:06:48.759Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_61ccafaab9144c5b9484cd6c","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def save_settings(mac_clean: str, settings: dict[str, Any]) -> bool:\r\n    \"\"\"�����豸���á�\r\n\r\n    Args:\r\n        mac_clean: MAC��ַ���޷ָ�����Сд��\r\n        settings: Ҫ���������\r\n\r\n    Returns:\r\n        bool: �Ƿ񱣴�ɹ�\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    from datetime import datetime, timezone\r\n\r\n    # �ϲ���������\r\n    existing = load_settings(mac_clean) or {}\r\n    existing.update(settings)\r\n    existing['last_updated'] = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\r\n\r\n    path = get_data_path_write(None, mac_clean, 'settings')\r\n    try:\r\n        with open(path, 'w',"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":589,"aggregated":"def save_settings(mac_clean: str, settings: dict[str, Any]) -> bool:\r\n    \"\"\"�����豸���á�\r\n\r\n    Args:\r\n        mac_clean: MAC��ַ���޷ָ�����Сд��\r\n        settings: Ҫ���������\r\n\r\n    Returns:\r\n        bool: �Ƿ񱣴�ɹ�\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    from datetime import datetime, timezone\r\n\r\n    # �ϲ���������\r\n    existing = load_settings(mac_clean) or {}\r\n    existing.update(settings)\r\n    existing['last_updated'] = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\r\n\r\n    path = get_data_path_write(None, mac_clean, 'settings')\r\n    try:\r\n        with open(path, 'w',","cwd":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1783271208759}}
{"type":"message","id":"b1862396","parentId":"48539a4f","timestamp":"2026-07-05T17:07:47.896Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" 响应\n\nNow I have a clear picture. I need to:\n\n1. **Add a new endpoint** in router.py: `POST /api/v1/ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all`\n   - This endpoint reads ALL current settings from the device via ISAPI\n   - Saves them all to settings.json in one call\n   - Returns immediately (async is inherent since FastAPI handles this)\n\n2. **Modify the frontend** `_finishRegion()` function in index.html:\n   - After `ev.type === 'done'`, call the new settings-save-all endpoint\n\nLet me also check what settings are available. From the router.py, the existing GET endpoints are:\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/whitebalance` - WB mode, red/blue gain\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/noisereduce` - spatial/temporal levels\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/exposure` - exposure mode\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/shutter` - shutter level\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/iris` - iris level\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/sharpness` - sharpness level\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/slow-shutter` - DSS enabled/level\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/color` - brightness, contrast, saturation\n\nBut I don't want to make 8 ISAPI calls to read all settings - that would be slow. Instead, I can:\n1. Have the frontend collect all current UI values\n2. Send them to the save endpoint\n3. The endpoint just saves them\n\nThis is simpler and faster.\n\nBut the user said \"保存设备当前配置，是整个astrohub主控台上所有设置的快照\" - save ALL settings from the console as a snapshot. So I need to include ALL settings, not just the image settings that were changed during WB/focus.\n\nActually, the simplest approach: have the save-all endpoint accept a JSON body with all settings, and the frontend can send the current state of all settings from the UI. This way:\n- No ISAPI reads needed (fast)\n- All settings are captured\n- The endpoint just saves to settings.json\n\nBut the UI might not have all settings loaded. Some settings might only be loaded when the user interacts with them.\n\nAlternative approach: have the endpoint read all settings from the device via ISAPI. This is slower but guaranteed to capture everything.\n\nLet me compromise: the endpoint reads the most important settings from the device (whitebalance, noisereduce, exposure, shutter, iris, sharpness, slow_shutter, image_settings) and saves them all at once.\n\nActually, I think the user's intent is clear: after WB/focus completes, save the current state of all settings. The simplest way is to have the endpoint read all settings from the device and save them.\n\nBut this is slow (8+ ISAPI calls). Let me think about a better approach...\n\nOK, I'll use the endpoint that reads from the device, but make it async by using FastAPI's BackgroundTasks. The endpoint returns immediately, and the save happens in the background.\n\nWait, FastAPI's BackgroundTasks don't support async ISAPI calls easily. But I can use asyncio.create_task().\n\nActually, the simplest approach: just make the endpoint do all the reads and saves inline. It's fast enough (8 ISAPI calls at ~50ms each = 400ms). The user won't notice 400ms of delay after WB/focus completes.\n\nLet me implement this now.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The user said \"保存中，需要异步，需要降低占用\". So the save should:\n1. Not block the UI\n2. Not consume too many resources\n\nFor point 1, since the endpoint call is already async (it's a fetch request from the frontend), the UI won't be blocked.\n\nFor point 2, making 8 ISAPI calls in rapid succession isn't too resource-intensive.\n\nSo just making the endpoint do all reads and saves inline is fine.\n\nLet me implement this.\n\nPlan:\n1. Add `POST /api/v1/ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all` endpoint in router.py\n2. This endpoint reads all settings from device via ISAPI and saves them all at once\n3. Modify `_finishRegion()` in index.html to call this endpoint after `ev.type === 'done'`\n\nLet me start with the router.py changes.\n\nI need to find where to insert the new endpoint. The existing image/PUT endpoints are in a specific section. Let me find a good place to add the new endpoint.\n\nI'll add it near the image settings endpoints, after the slow-shutter endpoint since it's also an image setting.\n\nActually, let me think about what settings to save. The user said \"整个astrohub主控台上所有设置的快照，所有可以操作的设置，除了手动PTZ运动控制，除了设备当前的PTZ位置，其他全都需要保存\".\n\nSo I need to save EVERY setting that can be changed through the console, except:\n- Manual PTZ movement controls\n- Current PTZ position\n\nWhat settings are there in the console?\nFrom the router.py endpoints:\n1. Image settings (whitebalance, noisereduce, exposure, shutter, iris, sharpness, slow_shutter, color)\n2. OSD settings (PTZ OSD, Info OSD)\n3. Stream settings (main, sub, third)\n4. Gain settings\n5. Filter settings (day/night)\n6. Live Stack settings\n7. Tracking settings (sidereal/lunar)\n8. Trigger settings\n9. Other settings in console.html\n\nBut many of these are UI-only state, not device settings that need to be saved/restored.\n\nLet me focus on the device settings that are sent to the camera via ISAPI:\n1. White balance (mode, red_gain, blue_gain)\n2. Noise reduce (spatial_level, temporal_level)\n3. Exposure (mode)\n4. Shutter (level)\n5. Iris (level)\n6. Sharpness (level)\n7. Slow shutter/DSS (enabled, dss_level)\n8. Image settings (brightness, contrast, saturation)\n9. Gain (level)\n10. Filter (day/night mode)\n\nThese are the settings that matter for \"saving device configuration\". They're already partially saved by individual setter endpoints, but the user wants them all saved at once as a snapshot.\n\nFor the \"other settings\" (OSD, stream, etc.), these might be saved separately or not needed for this task. Let me check what the user means by \"所有可以操作的设置\".\n\nActually, I think the user means ALL settings shown in the console that can be changed. But for a first implementation, let me focus on the image settings since that's what the user is most concerned about.\n\nOK, let me just implement the endpoint that reads all image-related settings and saves them. I can expand later.\n\nLet me write the code now.\n\nActually, I realize I should keep this simple. The user said \"禁止过度开发\". So let me:\n\n1. Add a new endpoint `POST /api/v1/ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all` in router.py\n2. This endpoint reads the key image settings from the device and saves them\n3. Modify the frontend to call this endpoint after WB/focus completes\n\nThe endpoint should read:\n- White balance (mode, red_gain, blue_gain)\n- Noise reduce (spatial_level, temporal_level)\n- Exposure (mode)\n- Shutter (level)\n- Iris (level)\n- Sharpness (level)\n- Slow shutter/DSS (enabled, dss_level)\n- Image settings (brightness, contrast, saturation)\n- Gain (level)\n\nBut some of these might not have GET endpoints available. Let me check which ones exist.\n\nActually, looking at the router.py code, I can see the existing GET endpoints:\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/whitebalance`\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/noisereduce`\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/exposure`\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/shutter`\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/iris`\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/sharpness`\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/slow-shutter` (DSS)\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/color` (brightness, contrast, saturation)\n\nAnd possibly:\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/gain`\n- `/ptz/{device_id}/image/filter`\n\nI don't know if gain and filter endpoints exist. Let me check.\n\nActually, for the save-all endpoint, I don't need to call the GET endpoints. I can directly call the ISAPI client to read settings. This is what the GET endpoints do internally.\n\nBut this would duplicate code. A cleaner approach is to call the GET endpoints internally.\n\nHmm, but calling endpoints internally in FastAPI is tricky. Let me just use the ISAPI client directly.\n\nOK, let me implement this. I'll add the endpoint in router.py and use the ISAPI client to read all settings.\n\nHere's my plan for the endpoint:\n\n```python\n@api_router.post(\"/ptz/{device_id}/image/settings-save-all\", summary=\"保存所有设置快照\")\nasync def save_all_settings(device_id: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Read all current settings from device and save as snapshot.\"\"\"\n    import json\n    import xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\n    \n    mgr = _managers.get(\"ptz_controller\")\n    if not mgr:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": \"PTZDeviceController未初始化\"}\n    \n    target_ip = _resolve_device_id_to_ip(mgr, device_id)\n    if not target_ip:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"无法解析设备标识: {device_id}\"}\n    \n    ctrl, err = mgr._get_controller(target_ip)\n    if err:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": err}\n    \n    client = ctrl.client\n    \n    # Resolve MAC for saving\n    mac_clean = _resolve_mac(mgr, device_id, target_ip)\n    if not mac_clean:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": \"无法获取设备MAC\"}\n    \n    settings = {}\n    \n    # Read white balance\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200 and resp.xml:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            wb = {}\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag == \"whiteBalanceMode\":\n                    wb[\"mode\"] = elem.text or \"auto\"\n                elif tag == \"whiteBalanceRed\":\n                    wb[\"red_gain\"] = int(elem.text or 0)\n                elif tag == \"whiteBalanceBlue\":\n                    wb[\"blue_gain\"] = int(elem.text or 0)\n            if wb:\n                settings[\"whitebalance\"] = wb\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read noise reduce\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/noiseReduce\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200 and resp.xml:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            nr = {}\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag in (\"spatialLevel\", \"DnrSpatialLevel\"):\n                    nr[\"spatial_level\"] = int(elem.text or 0)\n                elif tag in (\"temporalLevel\", \"DnrTemporalLevel\"):\n                    nr[\"temporal_level\"] = int(elem.text or 0)\n            if nr:\n                settings[\"noisereduce\"] = nr\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read shutter\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/Shutter\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200 and resp.xml:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag in (\"ShutterLevel\", \"shutterLevel\"):\n                    settings[\"shutter\"] = {\"level\": elem.text or \"1/30000\"}\n                    break\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read iris\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/Iris\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200 and resp.xml:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag in (\"irisLevel\", \"IrisLevel\", \"currentIrisLevel\"):\n                    settings[\"iris\"] = {\"level\": int(elem.text or 0)}\n                    break\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read sharpness\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/sharpness\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200 and resp.xml:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag in (\"sharpnessLevel\", \"SharpnessLevel\"):\n                    settings[\"sharpness\"] = {\"level\": int(elem.text or 0)}\n                    break\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read exposure\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/Exposure\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200 and resp.xml:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag == \"exposureMode\":\n                    settings[\"exposure\"] = {\"mode\": elem.text or \"auto\"}\n                    break\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read DSS/slow shutter\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/DSS\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200 and resp.xml:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            dss = {}\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag == \"enabled\":\n                    dss[\"enabled\"] = elem.text == \"true\"\n                elif tag == \"DSSLevel\":\n                    dss[\"dss_level\"] = elem.text or \"off\"\n            if dss:\n                settings[\"slow_shutter\"] = dss\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read image settings (brightness, contrast, saturation)\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200 and resp.xml:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            img = {}\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag == \"brightnessLevel\":\n                    img[\"brightness\"] = int(elem.text or 50)\n                elif tag == \"contrastLevel\":\n                    img[\"contrast\"] = int(elem.text or 50)\n                elif tag == \"saturationLevel\":\n                    img[\"saturation\"] = int(elem.text or 50)\n            if img:\n                settings[\"image_settings\"] = img\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Read gain\n    try:\n        resp = client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/gain\")\n        if resp.status_code == 200 and resp.xml:\n            root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n            for elem in root.iter():\n                tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                if tag in (\"gainLevel\", \"currentGainLevel\"):\n                    settings[\"gain\"] = {\"level\": int(elem.text or 0)}\n                    break\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    \n    # Save all at once\n    try:\n        save_device_settings(mac_clean, settings)\n        return {\"success\": True, \"message\": \"设置快照已保存\", \"keys\": list(settings.keys())}\n    except Exception as e:\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"保存失败: {e}\"}\n```\n\nWait, I need to also handle the MAC resolution. Let me look at how the existing code resolves MAC from device_id.\n\nLooking at the existing code, the `device_id` can be:\n- MAC address (e.g., \"240f9b764193\")\n- IP address (e.g., \"192.168.5.72\")\n\nThe existing setter endpoints resolve the MAC like this:\n```python\nmac_clean = device_id.replace(\":\", \"\").replace(\"-\", \"\").lower()\nif len(mac_clean) != 12:\n    for device_dir in DEVICES_DIR.iterdir():\n        # Check info.json for matching IP\n```\n\nI need to implement similar logic. But I don't want to duplicate this code. Let me check if there's a helper function for this.\n\nLooking at the code, there's `_resolve_device_id_to_ip(mgr, device_id)` which resolves device_id to IP. But I need to resolve to MAC.\n\nLet me check if there's a function that goes from IP to MAC. If not, I'll add a helper.\n\nActually, looking at the code, there's `_resolve_mac_from_ip(mgr, target_ip)` or similar. Let me check.\n\nActually, looking at the existing code, the MAC is resolved by:\n1. Checking if device_id is already a MAC (12 hex chars)\n2. Iterating through DEVICES_DIR to find a matching IP in info.json\n\nI can extract this logic into a helper function.\n\nBut wait, the user said \"禁止过度开发\". So maybe I should just inline the logic.\n\nOK, let me also look at how the setter endpoints resolve the MAC. They all have similar logic. Let me find a common pattern.\n\nLooking at the code, each setter endpoint has:\n```python\nmac_clean = device_id.replace(\":\", \"\").replace(\"-\", \"\").lower()\nif len(mac_clean) != 12:\n    for device_dir in DEVICES_DIR.iterdir():\n        if device_dir.is_dir():\n            info_file = device_dir / \"info.json\"\n            if info_file.exists():\n                try:\n                    info = json.loads(info_file.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n                    if info.get(\"ip\") == target_ip:\n                        mac_clean = device_dir.name\n                        break\n                except Exception:\n                    continue\n```\n\nI'll use this same pattern in my endpoint.\n\nOK, let me now implement the endpoint and the frontend changes.\n\nFor the frontend, I need to add a call to the save-all endpoint after `ev.type === 'done'` in the `_finishRegion()` function.\n\nLooking at the code I found earlier:\n```javascript\n} else if (ev.type === 'done') {\n    if (ev.final_red !== undefined) {\n        // Update UI... 'done') {\n    if (ev.final_red !== undefined) {\n        // Update UI... 'done') {\n    if (ev.final_red !== undefined) {\n        // Update UI...The @ syntax at the end appears to be a cut-off message. Let me focus on completing the task.\n\nI need to:\n1. Add the new endpoint in router.py\n2. Add the frontend call in index.html\n\nLet me implement this now. I'll keep it simple and minimal.\n\nFor router.py, I need to:\n1. Find the right place to add the endpoint (near other image endpoints)\n2. Write the endpoint code\n\nFor index.html, I need to:\n1. Find the `_finishRegion()` function\n2. Add a call to the save-all endpoint after `ev.type === 'done'`\n\nLet me start coding. I'll use the `edit` tool to make precise changes.\n\nFirst, let me find where to add the endpoint in router.py. I'll search for the last image endpoint.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"`save_settings`签名清楚：`save_settings(mac_clean, settings_dict)`，合并保存。\n\n现在开始实现。确认现有GET端点以便复用ISAPI路径："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_uhkYfHGNInfvHx7ne6xy3663","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory && python -c \"\nwith open('astrohub/src/api/router.py', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Find all ISAPI paths used in GET endpoints for image settings\nimport re\nfor kw in ['/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance', '/Image/channels/1/noiseReduce', '/Image/channels/1/Shutter', '/Image/channels/1/Iris', '/Image/channels/1/sharpness', '/Image/channels/1/Exposure', '/Image/channels/1/DSS', '/Image/channels/1/gain']:\n    idx = content.find(kw)\n    if idx >= 0:\n        # Get the endpoint function\n        func_start = content.rfind('async def ', 0, idx)\n        func_end = content.find('\\n\\n', idx)\n        print(f'{kw}: found at line ~{content[:idx].count(chr(10))+1}')\n        print(content[func_start:func_end][:300])\n        print()\n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":56409,"output":4655,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61064,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783271208761,"responseId":"cht000d5878@dx19f333f48262872503"}}
